"0#Expert communicator|Dan, I want to commend you on your expert communication skills. With the recent fantastic news about a new customer case study, in the sharing the goodness, the email responses from WHiQ feeling out of the loop and like we jumped too quickly to share could have been taken in a negative way, and you neutralized the tone, listened, and responded beautifully. You invited them in, suggesting ways to be more collaborative, and finding solutions going forward.  I saw the back and forth, and appreciate how well you handled it. Communicating is a fine art and requires great skill, and you do it well.\n\n1#Morgan Truck Body - case study approved!|Dan, Jess - I really appreciate the collaboration and tenacity with this case study. Back in September, we identified an opportunity to bring Morgan Truck Body's verbal words from HR Tech and bring them to life in a case study document that sales and marketing teams could use in programs. You quickly jumped at our request for writing help and took ownership of the copy and relationship. Which included nudging (A LOT) Brady at Morgan Truck Body for approval for months. We finally got it. Kudos to you both. I can't wait to see this in the wild. What a great story of how a customer uses recognition for offline workers!\n\n2#Enablement Improvements|Dan and Jess - can't thank you enough for your assistance in reviewing and improving the Workhuman Live sales and customer enablement assets.  Dan, after a brief early morning conversation on low enablement usage, you immediately set up time for a group meeting to review and analyze our assets.  Jess, your recommendations on how to better present and streamline the assets will allow us to equip the teams with tools they can use to drive registrations.   Much appreciated!\n\n3#Seismic Wiz|Jess and Dan, I wanted to thank you both for helping me so many times with updating and uploading the most recent versions of the mid-market configuration calculators for the sales team