eaderboard! You've gotten the most views on your Seismic LiveSend content over the last 30 days. Thanks for using Seismic, and keep rocking it!\n\n16#Team focused on highlight strengths|Team I want to thank each of you for dedicating your time to a very important project. There are many aspects of how we work with clients that we want to ensure we highlight during the sales process. Some of these are product related and others are the strength of our launch and program impact. This team is working to highlight some of these key areas to help the entire sales team best position the impact we make for our prospective new clients. Can't want to see what this team develops!!\n\n17#News You Can Use ‚Äì Story Contributors 08.24.2022|Team ‚Äì Thank you for contributing your ideas, voices, and skills to the Aug. 24 issue of News You Can Use. We couldn't have a best-in-class newsletter without people like you who step up to get things done and share what great looks like. Much gratitude!\n\n18#Thank you for helping our team grow!|Thank you all for your time and efforts in finding and interviewing our new Customer Education Content Manager, Jillian! Everything came together for a smooth and ultimately successful process ‚Äì from Daniella‚Äôs expert sourcing, the work it took to make this role ‚Äúofficial,‚Äù thorough interviews and feedback discussions, selling Jillian on the value of WH, and a thoughtful approach to the right offer. It wouldn‚Äôt have happened without each of you. Thank you again for helping grow our small but mighty Customer Communications & Education team!\n\n19#data needed for board week.. thank you|Jen & Dan thank you both this week for helping pass along some analysis needed to help support the board discussions. You both jumped in and help provide some great insights that were key to this weeks meeting.\n\n20#Part 2 of the Fab 5, Check!|Dan, Thank you for your help in fine-tuning the Accenture partnership content.  We're another step closer to creating a full proposal for our future joint clients!  Your quick turnaround also enabled me to present it during my Accenture meeting!  Thanks again for your support and giving it the proper care that will enable us to drive a successful joint GTM together!\n\n21#Competitive Intel|Brandon, thanks for sharing your knowledge to help us combat competitive traps as well as help us highlight the competitive differentiators we have. It is always extremely valuable to hear from folks who come from our space on how our competitors see us and how we should see ourselves, which can sometimes get foggy in the heat of battle. I also appreciated your perspective on the value of good discovery. Dan, thanks for your unwavering support in equipping the Midmarket team with the content, assets, and intel they need to close business. I appreciate having you as a partner.\n\n22#CHRO Moves|Dan - Fantastic initiative in working with and obtaining a new partnership to obtain recent CHRO moves as they happen.  We are only a few weeks into it and we are already seeing great results.  This is important to our organization as one of the most common themes in our wins is when former clients are involved.  The ability to see them move as it happens will go a long way to ensure we are working with the right people in the right place.\n\n23#Cheers to our First Global Workhuman Partner!|Team, THANK YOU for being a part of closing our very first global partner at Workhuman: Qualtrics!  Each of you played an essential role in helping throughout this partnership journey.  Your help brought us to where we needed to be, which included: shaping the story, advising on the process and people that need to be involved, coordinating the meetings, bringing our unique value and capabilities to life through presentations, creating a memorable experience for them, providing technical guidance, and formalizing the partnership through contract.  This partnership is the first of many, and the hard work begins here.  I couldn't have done this without you.  As I arrive at my first anniversary at Workhuman, I feel blessed to work with an amazing group of individuals (who also happen to be a lot of fun!).  Thank you again! ü•Ç #WorkhumanTogether\n\n24#Counting Content|Team - Thank you for the agility and responsiveness to a recent request for a summary of content in key areas of focus. You've all collaborated to create some impressive first fun content, and reacted swiftly with ideas on where and how to leverage it to support a broad set of upcoming initiatives. Appreciate that this was all done expertly and within a 24 hour turnaround period! Onward! -C\n\n25#Alexander Zimmerman, Sr.|Dan,  unbelievable job in gaining competitive intel from one of our great competitors.  In assuming your AKA identity you were able to gain great insights into what one of our competitors is doing as well as one of our more desired prospects.  On top of that you were able to capture and present back to the business all the relevant information.  thanks for always going above and beyond!!\n\n26#Coming through in a pinch!|Jess, Amanda and Dan, thanks so much for stepping up last minute to create some content for our meeting w/Rentokil.  The little details matter and when we came to you with a problem, you delivered timely and with quality.  Thanks so much for proving once again, that we work with the best team in the business!!\n\n27#Videographer|Dan, thank you for being the videographer to capture the #momentsthatmatter. Who knew so much could happen before the work day started on a Wednesday morning?!  This couldn‚Äôt have been made possible without you. Thank you!!\n\n28#It takes a Workhuman village! (part 2)|Last week was the culmination of the efforts by so many to bring the Executive Forum to life at Workhuman Live. Joining the team only 6 weeks before the event, I was blown away by the work ethic, camaraderie, and creativity of everyone involved. Your support, encouragement, and tireless commitment 