orite Holiday stories I want to thank you all for how you have led your teams in 2021 for the Past, Present, & Future of Business Ops at Workhuman.   In 2021 we have all had our share of obstacles and an extremely demanding set of deadlines and projects.   You have led all of those efforts with grace and made sure your teams had everything they need to deliver.  You have also done a fantastic job expanding and building your teams to what they are right now - and not just in team members, but it in terms team function.  We are now responsible for more than ever and your ability to lead from the front of that change has been inspiring.  Lastly, you have all prepared for the future.  Each of you have come up with great strategies for 2022 and how to bring even more to the company.  I thank each of you for your leadership and look forward to what 2022 has in store!!!!\n\n48#Take Aways and TAKING ACTION!!!|Dan and Jess - phenomenal job today running through your takeaways and initiatives from the Q4 QBR's.  You attended almost every single one, and you participated, listened, and more importantly, have already started action items.   You have already begun to shape some materials that can help everyone out now, and that is fantastic.  Its great having you with our group now, listening, hearing, and then helping us take action.  Great job!!\n\n49#Bringing in a Rock Star!|Team, Thank you for your support in being a part of the interview panel (and being on standby) and guidance throughout this process!  You were a part of helping me build my team and finding someone who can truly create a new world of possibilities in what this partner organization can bring.  You helped me find a rock star!  Thank you for being a part of this journey and helping to develop the growth of the partner organization. This is a new adventure with endless possibilities!\n\n50#Slam dunk on the IBM webinar|Team, I wanted to say thank you for doing such a great job on the recent IBM webinar promotions. Every contribution went a long way to drive one of our most highly registered-for webinars of the year. With over 900 people registered, and a 42% attendance rate, it surely was a hit! And sometimes, it the smallest things, like adding a ‚Äúwebinar tab‚Äù to our tile cards and social ads, that can make the biggest impact. I appreciate everyone on this team constantly putting forth their best efforts, making suggestions to try new things, for being open to feedback, and for being great partners. Webinars are one of the major MQL contributors and meeting drivers for Sales ‚Äì I can‚Äôt wait to see what this one brings in! Thank you all.\n\n51#Real Time Sales Enablement|Dan and Amanda - One of the biggest advantages to now having this group over with sales is the exposure we can get and the immediate impact we can have in real time.  In attending a QBR recently it was brought up that some fresh, more descriptive collateral around our Global capabilities could really help an ongoing deal we were close to the finish line on.  The two of you immediately went into action, creating not only something needed for that future customer, but something we can scale accordingly to the rest of the team.  Thank you for always looking for ways to help out and support the sales efforts!\n\n52#Beyond Grateful|Dan & Amanda, I have to take a quick moment to share my sincere gratitude for all the outstanding assets you both have been producing for the sales organization in recent weeks. I feel so incredibly supported, from the continued collaboration around understanding and improving the slides we use as SA's on sales calls to the outstanding Merck videos (and soon IBM videos) - you both do such important and collaborative work. Thank you!!\n\n53#Merck videos|Dan, A huge thank you and shout out for working with our amazing Merck story. I truly appreciate your partnership in taking the content and making it effective for sales. THANK You for recognizing its value for sales, leading the charge and making smaller cuts happen to really impact our sales efforts. Merck tells a great story and we've captured that nicely. You've taken the spirit and made it work for your teams. Massive thank you, Dan. It's appreciated.\n\n54#9/27 Marketing Newsletter Trivia Winners|Thanks for reading and participating in the marketing newsletter!\n\n55#Onboarding Dream Team!|Having a solid onboarding process is absolutely critical right now as the needs of the business are growing and changing. And if we think about all the connections that we make for our prospects with recognition - increased retention, boosting productivity, engagement, inclusivity...well, it's the same for onboarding! Each of you has played a key role in really dissecting what we do today and how we can be even better. As you know, doing the proper analysis (think discovery calls!) is so important to do upfront before we just go and build. Angela, you kept us all organized with your notetaking and I look forward to mapping out a project plan with you! Mary Jo, your support leading up to this was extremely helpful, taking the time to organize the session and make the most out of our 2 hours together. Dan, you and your team have already done so much work to contribute to onboarding improvements! We will identify some key focus areas and partner with you on developing additional assets. And Bashir, Lori, Jonathan, Sameer, and Ann-Marie - each of you offered valuable suggestions and feedback, some things which we can start to implement right away, others which might take some time to build out! Nonetheless, you were there - engaged in the discussion, committed to making change, all while balancing EOQ responsibilities, too. I can't thank each and every one of you enough. I am so grateful!\n\n56#Creating with Crayon|Dan,  I am so grateful for you/to you!  Thank you for taking the time to meet with me, listen to my suggestions in the Features Comparison for our Competitive Intelligence and taking all of