th putting into Seismic is paying off more and more all the time.  I know your vision was one place where we can finally find things and just wanted to tell you know, that is becoming the case more and more, and is greatly appreciated.  I wanted to make sure I told you directly, because heaven knows I was plenty willing to complain to you about the lack of findability in the past, and love to see us turning the corner.   üòâ  Thank you, I greatly appreciate and am benefiting from all your efforts!\n\n60#Always something new with this guy!!!|Dan,  it has been amazing the level of excellence you have brought to the sales org since joining in January, and its unbelievable the amount of content and tools you all put out what seems like every day.  Something new came out as I was writing this!!  You have done a fantastic job building your team and empowering them to do their best work.  We have thrown a lot at you in 2021, a lot of things that never quite could cross the finish line, and you picked up the baton and ran with it.  Thank you so much you do for all of sales!\n\n61#Better Educating to Our Future Customers|Dan, Amanda, Jess, Alan, Mark, Dave, Hari, Marcy, Corinne, Naomi, Meisha-Ann, Cam, Jay, Melanie, Amanda and Sarah - I wanted to take a moment to appreciate each of your contributions this past quarter as they've been key to developing assets that better educate our future customers. First and foremost - Dan, Amanda and Jess: thank you for your collaborative spirit and support through multiple iterations; the important and skillful work you do brings everything together! Alan, Mark, Dave & Hari: I want to thank you for the relentless focus you bring to each of our WHiQ slide reviews; your diverse perspectives and ability to communicate complexity in simple terms is what makes these meetings so informative and productive! Last but not least, Marcy, Corinne, Naomi, Meisha-Ann, Cam, Jay, Melanie, Amanda and Sarah, thank you for your deep partnership helping to 