ding the efforts to get everything collected, updated, and curated in one place.  At times it was like herding cats, but you did a phenomenal job always moving things forward.  No matter what else being worked on or trying to be completed by other deadlines, you stayed true to this vision.  I love how it came out, and I look forward to all the other ideas we still have for this project.  Thanks for all you do!\n\n67#Seismic slide library!|Dan, Amanda & Jess I want to thank each of you for the great work on the Seismic slide library for the sales team. Looks great to have all the decks in one place that can easily be viewed and sorted. This is really helpful to help give the team the information they need to help best position Workhuman. Thank you!\n\n68#Out with old, in with the new!!|Team,  I cant say enough about the planning, effort and execution into transforming the ability for sales to access ALL our slides.   We were looking to solve for a few things.  #1 convert the most popular and valuable slides to our new look and updated messaging.   #2 discover and collect the great one of slides that have been built over the years but have remained almost secretive.  #3 create new slides that sales has always wanted or needed.  This group worked tirelessly over the last 6 months.  Interviews with reps, working with marketing, creative and product, and the list goes on and on.  It was great to see it go up live today on Seismic and it looks great!  As we keep saying, its an ongoing journey and we have many slides to go, but we are on the right path!\n\n69#So glad you've joined sales!|Dan, Jess, and Amanda - I'm beyond thrilled you three are a part of the sales organization! Already, in my short time back from maternity leave, we've encountered countless projects and opportunities where we are/will partner together. I'm so grateful to get to work with each of you! I can always trust that you'll follow through with your action items and that all work will be done with a 