ng.  With all we are trying to achieve this year, I cant think of anyone better to be spearheading so many important things.\n\n84#Competitive Intelligence Focus|Dan thank you for your focus to help improve our competitive intelligence. First we need to collect everything we have and package it up in a way that can be useful. We also need to add in the pricing and positioning details that make it truly impactful. Appreciate your efforts and look forward to your results.\n\n85#Seismic and instant help|Dan and Jess - one, congrats again on your recent move internally! Two, and the reason for my Spark to you - both of you are always nearly INSTANT when it comes to helping out or answering questions. I asked you this morning to help one of our new hires out getting setup with Seismic, it was done in minutes. Recently I had some questions for you guys on content, Seismic, and few other related things and again, almost instant to respond and get me what I needed and on my way. It's truly game changing to get help and answers so quickly when we're trying to get things done. I truly appreciate it and you both as I know the whole sales org does. Thank you!\n\n86#DE&I Exellence|Dan and Jess,  thank you so much for the hard work you both put into building out new collateral for the Sales Team around DE&I.  The messaging, the graphics, and the information was outstanding.  It now gives the entire team the tools to have a great conversation with future customers as well as giving them the knowledge needed for the topic to have an educated conversation.  You have only just started with Sales but you both are already making such a great impact.  Thank you!\n\n87#News You Can Use - Story Contributors|Brian, Chris, Dan, Jen, Jenn, & Tim; We couldn't have a best-in-class newsletter without fine folks like yourselves who put themselves out there and share what great looks like. Thank you for taking time out of your day to share what is working! Much gratitude!\n\n88#No wine, but lots 