man  video's helped to get conversations going with other organizations when Covid was peaking in Europe. Thanks again for all the work involved in putting these together.\n\n95#Seismic Recording|Thank you for taking the time to partner on the Seismic Workday training recording. It was great working through this with you and I appreciate the extra time you took out of your day to help support this initiative.\n\n96#2021 Marketing Planning Pros!|So, we didn‚Äôt quite spend 6 hours together today but pretty close to it! Add in previous working sessions, the pre-work PLUS the work to come, and we will easily surpass that. BUT in the end, we'll be poised and ready to execute a solid plan for the new year. We appreciate your commitment to the 2021 marketing planning process. We‚Äôre taking a different approach this year and we‚Äôre coming close to the 10-month mark of working remotely during an epic year of CRAZY. With so many players involved, different points of view, and known foundational gaps like solid messaging ‚Äì (YES, we know, we know!)‚Ä¶it‚Äôs not an easy task. We are optimistic about the progress we‚Äôre making together. We are grateful for your focus on the end goal and how we'll get there. Thank you for partnering with us to sharpen our strategies and set our teams up to properly support the business in 2021. Onward we go! Z + Amy\n\n97#Pivot and Proceed!|Thank you both for your quick response and strategic insight to launch a recap of the Evanta UK CHRO Town Hall to attendees. It was great to work together to balance timeliness with content effectiveness, in order to provide attendees with key messages and learnings from the event. I appreciate your willingness to pivot on a plan, share solutions based on best practices, and take action quickly, in order to provide our sales team with the necessary information for their follow-up. Appreciate your team work here!\n\n98#Congrats Workhuman Live Team!|Team ‚Äì A HUGE shout out to each of you for helping deliver a fantastic event yesterday. It truly was amazing! Your hard work and dedication to excellence have set a NEW example for everyone in our organization. I‚Äôm inspired by the ingenuity and creativity of everyone‚Äôs contribution ‚Äì planning, marketing, storytelling, vendor management, customer support, technical execution, and so much more. Your efforts have allowed us to create a new conversation in the marketplace. I‚Äôm genuinely excited to build on this shared momentum to help every organization bring people closer together. None of this would be possible without YOU. I extend my heartiest congratulations on achieving a fantastic milestone. Well done ALL!\n\n99#Certified Bug Hunters!|I wanted to take a moment to call out this amazing group of humans for answering the call to hunt for bugs as we test the Workhuman Certified Enterprise website and platform. This team went above and beyond, bringing a critical eye to all areas of the program and providing so much amazing feedback that will help us improve our customer experience, site performance and messaging at launch and beyond. Thank you!\n\n100#Offsite virtually, but totally productive day IRL!|Team ‚Äì Thank you for your active participation in our 2nd planning ‚Äúvirtual‚Äù offsite. The energy level was high and the level of engagement and strategic thinking was strong. Patti and I are excited about the united approach to not only long-term marketing planning, but building a strong culture for the entire Marketing team where different points of view are embraced and we are continually testing new ways of working to optimize our contributions to overall business results. I‚Äôm genuinely excited to build on this shared momentum to bring our 2021 plans to life. With gratitude ‚Äì C.\n\n101#Making Work Human Book Published Today!|Today is launch day!  Making Work Human.  And the first thing to say is THANK YOU to you and indeed to all of Workhuman, because this book is our story, our experiences, our client case studies, our insights from the data, our reflections and years of working together, put into a book.   It takes village to publish a book, and we want to call out and recognize the core book publishing team and those who played a pivotal role at a pivotal moment.  Doug Hardy, Kevin Mullins, Dan Miller, Lynette Heelan, Jessica Klay, Carrie Rogers, Maureen Buxton, and all of whom worked directly on the content and project management for this book, professionals in every way, without whom this day would not have been possible.  Thank you all for making a difference in the world and bringing this book to be published today.\n\n102#üôåüèª Upleveling our Team Updates üôåüèª|Week in and week out, each of you contribute to a few different communication vehicles we have to keep our team and stakeholders across the company up to date on all the amazing things that are happening in the world of Marketing. About a month or so ago, I came to the team with a new process for pulling together our weekly updates and challenged each of us to think about the intended audience and what would be most valuable to them...We started including more metrics and other performance data in our look-backs and introduced headlines to provide more focus. We are also incorporating more visuals to keep the content fresh and engaging. We held each other accountable to sticking to a standard template and hitting deadlines so that we could get the updates edited and out the door in a timely fashion. I know between the weekly marketing updates, the digital programming status reports and ELT progress updates, you probably feel like this is communication overload at times, but they are important in staying connected and current especially when we are all remote. I sincerely appreciate your part in helping to improve the quality. THANK YOU!\n\n103#Thanks for always having a minute.|Dan, really appreciate how you and your team are always there to lend a hand even with little to no notice. The most recent example is you stepping in to guide content and streamline production of Patti's \"Have a Minute?\" series. Thank you for being the consummate team player and a shining example of selfless leadership!\n\n104#Moving Moments|Thank you all for playing an integral role in our Change Management workshop to work through how to effectively roll out DG 2.0 to sales. Your input will help inform the strategy and ensures we are taking your day-to-day processes into account when working through all of these new initiatives. Thank you again for dedicating a few hours of your day to this discussion and ensuring a solid partnership between marketing and sales.\n\n105#Evanta Follow-Up Fortitude|Your thoughtful and creative efforts lead to a multi-pronged follow-up approach from our Evanta D, E, & I virtual town hall - reaching such an important audience. Within one day of the event, you created a blog post, updated landing pages to make the book available to these attendees, provided video solutions, organized and customized campaigns, and launched outreach in a timely manner to aid sales in their outreach efforts. Your willingness to go above and beyond in such a short timeframe is valued and appreciated, while your level of detailed communication led to the production of impactful, meaningful content that will have the greatest impact on this program.\n\n106#Hello Workday!|Thank you for being an early adopter of Workday and for completing your scavenger hunt by the end of our first day officially live!!\n\n107#Customer Stories Squad!|Team! Thank you so much for the partnership on curating our latest customer stories into a single spot. With new folks constantly joining the organization, its so critical we streamline these pieces of content to get the most mileage of out them. So thrilled the team was able to think outside of the box and develop an interim solution that will help us keep organized ahead of Seismic launch in the fall. GO TEAM and so excited to begin phase 2 of this project.\n\n108#Content Power Team!|Dan, Sarah, and Jess - This is so overdue, and I wanted to recognize you on your teamwork and willingness to always help with ANY request that comes in from the marketing teams. Whenever we're trying to identify scope and content pieces, your collaboration is so appreciated and we're always able resolve so quickly. Your team produces such impactful work, and it's been a pleasure working with you all!\n\n109#Virtual Offsite - but 100% Productive IRL|Team - On behalf of Patti and myself thank you for a tremendous Q3 strategic planning and execution offsite last week. Both presenters and discussion partners excelled in their roles to communicate and strengthen existing plans. Your engagement and participation was locked in for the full session. And it's exciting to see this team rally around a new way of working that is oriented toward connecting business results to the strategic objectives of all our 2H initiatives within Marketing and across partner stakeholder teams. Thanks for leaning into the process - it's becoming a difference maker for us and helping us cut through our own noise! -C\n\n110#Teamwork Makes the Content Work|Team! Thanks so much for taking a good chunk of your time this week to discuss content mapping for customers in Q3 and beyond. It was such a productive and thoughtful conversation. Everyone came to the meeting with thoughts and ideas and I cannot thank Dan, Sarah and Jess enough for being so open minded, honest and putting the customer experience first! I'm excited to test, learn and continuously improve. Go team!\n\n111#Seismic here we come...|Chris and Dan, I wanted to call out the speed of help and support I received from both of you this past week.  I hopped onto an implementation call thinking this was nice information to have not realizing that Customer Success was part of the roll-out and I would have some homework.  Without hesitation you both jumped into action.  Chris, the very next day you spent some time walking me through the product to ensure I had a general understanding of what Seismic was and its capabilities.  Dan, that day you ensured we had a demo scheduled with me and a smaller Team to ensure we understood the product, expectations and next steps..not to mention the homework deliverables  :)  Thank you both for taking time out of your already busy schedules to help bring me up to speed.  This is going to be a huge win for Sales, Customer Success and WH as a whole!!!\n\n112#Collaboration at its finest|Dan and Jess, thank you both for being patient and open-minded with the feedback we had on a recent content asset to be used in our demand gen campaigns. You could have chosen to be frustrated that we were straying from the original direction, but instead you welcomed the feedback and we had an extremely collaborative and productive discussion. I love that we were all able to hit the pause button and take a few steps back to figure out the best way forward. The original asset was good, but the enhancements we‚Äôre going to make will really help it resonate with our target audience. I have no doubt we‚Äôre going to knock this one out of the park! Thanks for the collaboration, for being open to receiving feedback and for the continued partnership between our teams!\n\n113#Measurement for success|A bit late but I wanted to thank you all for your dedication, collaboration, and teamwork as we solidified measurements for Awareness, Perception and Preference. Learning and listening to each other through every meeting, I saw such great passion for accuracy and full transparency in the unknown. We worked together to present solid recommendations, and received great feedback. With our next steps to operationalize, use Q1-Q2 2020 as litmus on measurements, and prepare for QBRs together we'll create the best measurable Brand marketing we've ever had. I couldn't be more proud of this team.\n\n114#You've got this covered.|Thank you to this team for comprehensive coverage of our session at Total Resilience. Dan and Sarah, thank you for building the conference into the overall content plan and for moving up the promotion post to give more time to promote Rob‚Äôs session. Aaron, thank you for pulling together the promotion blog that shared our overall presence at the event. Sarah, thank you for attending the session and writing a follow-up post that beautifully summarized the key takeaways. Holly, thank you for writing up social posts for both our Workhuman channels and for our speaker - excited to build this into the process for speakers moving forward. Jess, thanks for your help getting everything into Elevate for easy sharing. And Max, thank you for attending on the day to live tweet the session. I know I can always count on all of you and I'm grateful for your collaboration.\n\n115#Last minute request support|Thanks for pitching in on a VERY last minute request for the HR Pulse magazine fall issue!\n\n116#Making Work Human|The journey to publishing a book is a long one. So much work behind the scenes to ensure it's top notch, well-written, and a fantastic testament to the thought leadership and vision of the authors and company. Now imagine being at the finish line and a pandemic hits.    Imagine pushing the book back given the uncertainty in the world. Now imagine in the midst of all this, the book becoming better with an opportunity to update it to reflect the new realities and the social injustices in the world.  Thank you Dan for all the work to bring it across the finish line (a second time!). This is a book that brings the thought leadership and writings of Eric, Derek, and Workhuman to new levels!\n\n117#Mining networks for Keeping Work Human guests!|We launched the Keeping Work Human video series back in March as a way to lead through COVID-19, and then we started a conversation about racial inequity, and now we're looking forward to what's next. For the last 3-4 months we've recorded video interviews with 1-5 guests a week from across not only the HR leadership space, but from our own lives. All of you have contributed to this effort by working your networks, asking the customers and future customers you talk to, helping me reschedule guests when a conflict arises (huge hat tip to Daisy and Lauren!), convincing your friends and family members to come on, and simply keeping the video series in mind as you go about your daily lives. I couldn't keep this thing going day in and day out without the steady stream of guest suggestions, scheduling help, and introductory emails. Thank you for connecting us with the 40+ guests we've had the pleasure of speaking with and getting to know over the course of this show (and helping me with the logistics, too). It's been a massive team effort and I'm glad to have the chance to finally recognize this group!\n\n118#Leading with Humanity|Dan - I just want to express my gratitude for your human-centered approach to leadership always, but especially these past few months. You've led our team through truly unprecedented times. You've been clear about expectations and consistent in your communication. You're always understanding of the various work/life balance challenges the pandemic has presented. And you continue to focus on removing barriers and helping us do our best work. It will be great to finally meet in person at some point, but I've enjoyed our weekly walking 1/1s and your steady and calm advice for navigating our team through the many pivots in strategy. Thank you for leading with humanity!\n\n119#What Makes Us Human: Heart and Soul|Team, when most of us are feeling defeated, deflated, and hopeless, each of you came together to unite our hearts and souls with the people we most want to reach. I shed more than one tear experiencing the imagery and messages of hope and pragmatism. Your respect, empathy, and compassion for all hearts and souls inside and outside of our company has made an impact.  Thank you for transforming a sad exception to our lives into one that brings us together instead of dividing us all.  As always, thank you for your hard work and determination to Workhuman. Best, Patti\n\n120#Amazing Content|Amazing content team. I was doing a bit of work this afternoon, working on some messaging and themes for the Chris French email. One of the things I needed to do was gather up content on the topic of next normal as we all adjust to different ways of working. As I searched our incredible resource center, it got me thinking what an AMAZING content team we have. I found everything I needed with ease and it reminded me of just how impressive of a feat this team accomplished in such short time to crank our relevant and useful content to our key audiences. Cheers to this amazing group!\n\n121#Inspiring leadership|Dan ‚Äì Every workday since at least mid-April, you have sent an email to your team (Sarah, Aaron, Lynne, and me) simply titled \"Inspiration.\" These messages contain short passages intended to ignite gratitude, energy, courage, hope, or another empowering, positive emotion. Some days, the mornings are too busy to fully read and internalize the message ‚Äì but I make sure to look at it before I log off and it helps remind me of why I'm working so hard, in collaboration with all these fantastic people, to get Workhuman's messages and solutions out into market where they can help people and organizations all over the world. Thank you for everything you do to keep us feeling not only motivated and energized, but also appreciated, heard, and supported. You're a real champion and I'm grateful for your leadership.\n\n122#Social Media Livestream power players!|Thank you to this group of social media power users! You each contributed 5+ posts during the week of Workhuman Livestream, contributing to a company record of over 500 employee posts in a single day. Well done!\n\n123#Fierce commitment to urgency|\"We are now faced with the fact that tomorrow is today. We are confronted with the fierce urgency of now. In this unfolding conundrum of life and history, there IS such a thing as being too late. This is not time for apathy or complacency. This is a time for vigorous and positive action.\" - MLK JR.   Team, since I started just over a month ago, I have heard from many of you and our stakeholders who have talked about the misfortune of joining Workhuman during a global pandemic that has changed every thing about how we live: from how we interact, to what we spend our time and money on, what we value, and how we work.  The truth is, there was no better time for me to be able to witness the magic that is Workhuman. We already know what is important and that is human connection. What you have demonstrated is humanity during a time of extreme urgency - a rarity in life and certainly in business. Thank you for your passion for your and your commitment to each other and our stakeholders.  I am honored to work alongside each of you.\n\n124#Moodtracker Launch success!|Team ‚Äì Thank you for delivering our brand new Moodtracker product. Thank you so much to everybody for the amazing work on the Moodtracker product. Hard to believe this was just an idea at the beginning of January. Since then a team has formed, the product designed, architected, built, tested, branded, communicated, marketed and launched. Whew. The speed at which the groups collaborated is a tribute to the sense of camaraderie and positivity we have at Workhuman. The energy, imagination has shone through in every way. This coupled with the determination to deliver a world-class product means that today we have a sixth edition to our Workhuman Cloud suite. Welcome Moodtracker. On behalf of all of the humans in the company, thank you. Eric.\n\n125#Moodtracker GTM Content Excellence|Dan and Jess ‚Äì I love getting the chance to work with my old Content neighbors, especially on the big stage of a new product launch (combined with a major online event!). Dan, you‚Äôre a pro at finding the right tone and messaging for the live blog, and yesterday you were a natural partner in the Moodtracker go to market strategy. Jess, you truly drove the success of the infographic, not only providing the copy but working with Kevin to get the visuals looking great. Not only that, you both made sure you were available for proof reading and content review on all Moodtracker and post event materials (as well as customer logo advice!) I know this week is only the beginning, and I can‚Äôt wait to collaborate more with you both very soon!\n\n126#Spotlight Speaker Success Stories|Team - thank you for stepping into the spotlight during our last three marketing town halls. You‚Äôve shown at an exemplary level of innovation, determination, and grit amidst our new normal. You‚Äôve conveyed your success stories (Merck webinar, Keeping work human series, and WHL) with an awesome combination of humility and accessibility. Thank you, thank you, thank you for being leaders of the moment and in the moment. The best practices you‚Äôve shared and modeled to achieve such high levels of success are great guideposts and shining examples of a high performing culture ! Well done and with gratitude, -C\n\n127#Meaningful Words|Dan and Sarah, thank you for always being there to put word to the things we need to say.  So many of our efforts stem from an idea.  A concept.  A bundle of thoughts ‚Äì which can be interpreted may ways and have different meanings for our many audiences.  You once again stepped up to tackle a challenge we faced with putting meaningful words and clear objectives to a project, that is helping all the teams take action in the market.  Thank you for your help and support.\n\n128#Yahoo for Customer Content!|Dan, Sarah and Jess - thanks so much for the partnership over the last few weeks to help crank out some great customer content. You have been so helpful, responsive and thinking outside of the box to help brainstorm ways to get some rich and thoughtful bits in front of our customers in a time when they need it most. All of this when I know you have the fullest of full plates on lots of other important content! Thanks for being such a great partners and collaborators!\n\n129#Making us stronger together - every single day|Team - what a week! I am blown away by your collective and individual innovation. These are the experiences that can give us the best learnings and insights - not only in terms of skills, but more important, learning just how much awesomeness we are capable of bringing to the world. Thank you. Onward!\n\n130#Checking In, Checking Success!|Amy, Dan, and Katie - Every morning at 9 since we've been at home due to COVID-19, we've checked in together with our video calls.  You've shared not only amazing ideas and suggestions but also worries and concerns as we navigate so many interesting paths as a company, culture, and team. Thank you for your willingness to be so open, as it's a critical ingredient for trust and ultimate success.  And boy, has there been success!  Incredible achievements across PR, content, and social.  Anyone looking at our social feeds can see your work and leadership on a daily basis and see how it's propelling our brand and company higher and higher. Thank you for all of your work (and teamwork) as we continue to show how Workhuman can help elevate human connections across the world!  Kevin\n\n131#One Team|Dan and Jess, I can‚Äôt thank you enough for all the proofing you‚Äôve done over the past week as we prepared for the launch of free products. There has been a LOT of copy created with all kinds of quick turnarounds - and since it‚Äôs never ideal for writers to proofread their own work, I knew I could come to you. Jess - you‚Äôve had your keen eyes on all the social posts for the Keeping Work Human series and all the social ads for the launch of free WHCT. Dan - you reviewed the entire microsite copy this morning in record time and when I thanked you for doing so, you said ‚ÄúWe‚Äôre one team.‚Äù We sure are. I appreciate you both so very much.\n\n132#Helping Excellence Become A Reality|Along with Rosette and the team (Omar, Naomi, Amanda and Krista) we would like to thank this amazing group of colleagues who joined us with little notice to be the Alpha Testers  of a new workshop we have created for prospects and maybe even customers ‚Äì  Keeping Work Human.  Like the judges on America‚Äôs Got Talent, you silently sat then gave your direct, candid review verbally (and then used Conversations to deliver the feedback in writing).   You shared your collective wisdom, gave us thoughts on how to improve and then hit the gold button - so next stop is to take the show on the road.  Off to TX we (virtually) go to deliver this to USAA and there is a potential of General Mills in Minnesota next and maybe even Memorial Hermann Health System  Rosette and all of us that worked many hours on this workshop  appreciate you all so much for jumping with little notice and helping us all prepare to deliver excellence.\n\n133#Making COVID Connections for Merck|While we're still in the process of creating a webinar for Merck, I had to pause and appreciate the amount of effort that has gone into creating an exceptional experience and one that ties into the current pandemic situation. In the span of the week, we've pivoted and changed the focus of the webinar altogether to be timely, considerate and ties into concerns of the greater HR community, while also being in line with the vision that our contacts at Merck have. That includes multiple revisions of content, shepherding and managing approvals of interested parties. Not to mention creating a final piece that will speak to the strong partnership we have with Merck, as well as the human messaging we want to have in the market. Despite the constant changes, I walk away from of all of our brainstorming sessions feeling energized and excited at the story we are weaving, supplemented by WARI data. Thank you all for the talent, commitment and passion you have brought and continue bringing to this effort.\n\n134#Sharing is caring|High 5s to you 5 fine humans! Why you ask? I pulled together a marketplace update over the weekend but with more than a dozen companies to track, I knew I could not do it alone. I asked the marketing leaders who could help out and Dan and John - you both didn't blink raising your hand to chip in. Dan - your team is cranking out thoughtful content every day but you generously offered to let Jess H help with this. John - first you said you could ask your team to help but then you decided to take on the extra workload yourself! Jess - you were quick, thorough and proactively reached out to me with your specific updates throughout the week. But, as the week went on and our COVID related scope of work kept growing, I knew I had to reassess how we resourced the efforts so that we could provide timely updates to Sales and the entire organization. Pam - I went to you next and asked if I could enlist Mark's help. And you too, didn't hesitate a second. You quickly talked to Mark and followed up to tell me he'd be in touch. Within hours, Mark not only proactively reached out to me for the download but he took the project on with ease and enthusiasm and delivered a new update of today's marketplace COVID related activity Hugely valuable. Thank you all! I love this team and this great example of teamwork at its finest.\n\n135#Leaning on the Experts|Guys, I really appreciate your support over the last few days as we worked through the details of the video series. Thank you for sharing your input on how this should work, look, and be delivered to the audience. We‚Äôre moving so fast and making decisions quickly, and doing that well is only possible when we trust the team around us. I‚Äôm extremely grateful to each of you for sharing your expertise!\n\n136#Calm support through trying times|Hi team ‚Äì I want to commend you for rallying together across content and social to streamline processes, align on calendars, and communicate with calmness and clarity across teams. Dan, Sarah, and Lauren ‚Äì no one works in a vacuum, and I don't thank you enough for your editorial support, not just now but always. I appreciate the opportunities you've provided to be brave in my writing and confident in my editing and leadership. Max ‚Äì I was looped in late to the current #RecognizetheGood campaign and you fielded my questions about how to translate it to Elevate, checked my work, and even hopped on a last-minute call to talk through it. Holly and Roshni ‚Äì you're both so busy, but you've been there to fearlessly offer guidance and support and help make everything as efficient as possible as we all figure out our way through this. Thank you all for your part in making this week (how is it only Tuesday?!) much easier than it could have been. You're the best.\n\n137#Dan the Man!|Dan - special call out to recognize the outsized contribution you‚Äôve made to the COVID campaign. The editorial calendar you created and over-delivered on today is the lynchpin of this initiative. Thank you for showcasing agility and commitment to the business at a time when we are all being pulled in lots of directions - with gratitude -C\n\n138#It's Go Time!|Team - I wanted to first say thank you for your rapid response to the business's need for a COVID rapid response campaign. I also want to acknowledge that working at this pace and with a level of uncertainty may be new and/or uncomfortable, but that has not stopped this group from leaping into action, mobilizing, and being agile and responsive to rapidly evolving priorities - including stopping existing work, pivoting planned content, and being open-minded about new ways of working team together and team apart (as we leverage remote technology for the next while). Still lots to do, and I'm confident with the cohesion demonstrated this week we will do great things that help our current and future customers navigate uncertain times and that we will unlock new approaches and agility as a cross functional team. Thank you all. With gratitude, -C\n\n139#Words of Wisdom|Every day, we have to make decisions in our jobs and life.  Not just about what to do ‚Äì but how to react.  And no matter our role, title or years of experience ‚Äì questioning yourself in the moment is normal.  But it never feels good.  Dan, you recently observed me doing just that.  Juggling some decisions and actions, while debating and questioning every one of them in the process.  You took a moment to quietly approach me and offer a few words of wisdom and encouragement.  You related some of your own experiences and helped me have the confidence to forge forward on my path.  Thank you for taking that brief moment out of your day for me (and really ‚Äì it was all of two minutes we chatted).  It meant a lot to me, and was truly impactful.\n\n140#November 21, 2019|Assuming Outlook is accurate, November 21, 2019  was our first official \"Marketing Directors meeting.\" Sixteen weeks later, I wanted to take a moment to personally thank each of you for ALLLL the time and energy you've invested in our time together. We've been meeting on a weekly basis  to establish more visibility, create more alignment across functional teams, collaborate on short and long term planning, negotiate budgets, brainstorm core marketing themes, discuss better ways of working together...the list goes on an on. And while I know we all cringe at the thought of another meeting on our calendars when we are starved for time, I strongly believe if we come together on a regular basis and focus on the right things, we'll all be smarter for it. I have so much gratitude for each of you! Thank you and see you next Wednesday!\n\n141#Helped me find my voice, quite literally!|Publishing my first article in Forbes was big moment for me and ironically, all the things I shared quite literally were a part of how this came together. Amy, thanks for the steady push to share my voice. You have been a staunch supporter guiding with a firm yet gentle hand. Lynne, you got the ball rolling, talking with me, helping make sense out of my myriad thoughts and seeing a story, putting them in writing in a great cohesive way. Dan, you steadily provided guidance and resources. Dave, you leaned in immediately when you heard my frustration, rolled up your sleeves and channeled my voice through rounds 4, 5 and 6. Sarah, you are just magical with your editing style. You took version 6 and over the weekend edited for crispness and polished in a way that made me feel eloquent and clever. I am grateful for this agile team that came together to ironically help me find my voice in print! Thank you all for helping me take my own darn advice: taking that first step. Here's to many more!\n\n142#Spare a moment for a proof?|Dan, Sarah - I've been using these short words often lately and I want to take a moment to say thank you for all your support. While the phrase is sort, the requests are not! From reviewing press releases, to Forbes blog posts to byline articles, the timeliness and rigor you put into reviewing the content is much appreciated!\n\n143#Constructs for success|A few weeks ago we took on a herculean task, gathering a small cross-functional team to create a rubric for consistent messaging heading into 2020. 19 core narratives, from themes to products, and the building began. Each of you played a part, both large and small and we are off to a such a strong start! Next steps are culling these down even more to get them over the finish line but I couldn‚Äôt have done any of this without your help and support. GO TEAM!\n\n144#Interview dream team|A sincere THANK YOU to all of you for your participation in interviews over the past few months, for our Director of Product Marketing. Someone of you met with 5 candidates - which adds up to a LOT of time out of your schedules. Some of you only met with a couple of finalist candidates, but helped us to wrap up the search and make important decisions about who we were hiring. Overall, you all were so responsive, flexible, open-minded and just a pleasure to work with throughout this process. Thank you so much for the part you played in getting this fill across the finish line!\n\n145#Copy + Content = Collaboration|Dan and Jess, I just want to thank you both for being such great partners around the editorial and copy guidelines, and how we stay aligned and consistent in what we produce -- especially since I've crossed over to Creative. I value our collaboration so much and I continue to admire your collective level of commitment to quality and consistency. And you know you're both my favorite people to nerd out with over some grammar rules. Long live the Oxford comma!\n\n146#Making Making Work Human|Dan - I want to commend all of your fantastic work on the Making Work Human book. The journey to book completion is a long one. So many drafts, reviews, inputs, approvals, and more. Through it all, you have been so steady, focused, and dedicated to quality. You have reviewed the book so many times I'm sure you can recite it word for word! Your meticulous approach to detail is the perfect attribute toward ensuring what goes into market represents the best of Workhuman and Eric and Derek. Thank you for all of your efforts thus far. The end is near (though it many ways, the opportunities are just beginning!)  Kevin\n\n147#Amazing team support|I wanted to take a moment to say a big Thank You. You guys have been an amazing support for me since I started in Jan. Always so happy to jump in, point me in the right direction and producing amazing content. Really happy to be working with you guys!\n\n148#Feedback|Dan - Thank you for taking time to send me feedback. It was also very timely! I know these requests can be time consuming but they are very helpful! I am grateful for our partnership and relationship.\n\n149#Ask and you shall receive|Twice, I've recently come to you with simple enough asks regarding our new book. Twice, you immediately responded during your own busy day, providing me with the exact thing I was looking for - no questions asked. Thank you, Dan, for being a great teammate and sharing information that you know is critically beneficial to our team!\n\n150#Always On Communication|Dan, I feel like this is quite overdue. I want to commend you on ALWAYS putting communication first. No matter how much you have going on, no matter how many meetings, deadlines or initiatives; you still miraculously find the time to walk over and spend time just sharing updates and ensuring we are all aligned; critical when we are moving so swiftly. Thank you for always being a top notch listener and an all around star of a teammate - GO DAN!\n\n151#Helping to build a culture of \"I see you\"|Team #15!! Thank you for your active  participation in our Ignite Solutions brainstorm session. I really appreciate that you all contributed, you built off each other's ideas, you purposefully included the facilitator as a contributor (thank you Stacey) and most of all you came up with some really great ideas on how we can keep our culture feeling \"small\" as we continue to grow, how we can better connect with our colleagues, and create moments that matter. Your efforts made the session successful and made my job as the facilitator super easy. I look forward to our ideas coming to life. You all proved the power of the Workhuman culture/zeitgeist!\n\n152#Focus on Improvement and Growth|Dan - I wanted to commend your work over the past couple of months on bringing Seismic to our attention. Great job in taking a step back and thinking about software solutions that could elevate our ability to help sales (and create more consistency for content). Your approach was thoughtful, thorough, and smart. While we have not crossed the finish line yet, I did want to call out your great leadership from the very beginning.  Well done!\n\n153#Super helpful messaging framework|Dan -  thank you for putting together a comprehensive messaging framework for Eric and Derek's new book. As we start to seed the market with key themes from the book, I've found it a helpful reference in creating new content and editing content to ensure messaging alignment. I really like the way you organized the document, with key messages about what readers will get out of the book at the beginning and quick recaps of each chapter. I know I'm not the only one who will benefit from your work here. And as a side note, thank you for also for keeping me and others consistently updated on progress of the book so we're all on the same page. Great job!\n\n154#WH News - last story of the year!|Dan ‚Äî I wanted to take a moment to thank you for  letting us cover your experience dancing in The Nutcracker in last week‚Äôs WH news feature story. Your understanding that these different life experiences and accomplishments are some of our most engaging pieces of content is really appreciated. You were such a pleasure to interview! Your answers were so thoughtful, descriptive, and your ties back into how this life experience outside of work has a direct correlation to your work at Workhuman were spot on. You agreed to this interview the week of, and set-up a meeting the very next day. Not only did you provide us with such great content, you also took the time to read through and make some edits for us. I appreciate you!\n\n155#Bite-sized marketing updates, Buffet-sized results|Great job all on your collective sharings and updates during our full marketing team meeting this week. There is so much goodness happening in marketing right now and each of you showcased the strategic thinking, approach, and results in a very concise way. And...you also stayed on time! This shows how each of you respect each other and the full marketing team. It also ensured that everyone had an opportunity to share their work and create greater alignment across the entire group.  Thank you!\n\n156#Thank you!|I want to thank you for taking time out of your busy schedule to meet with me to discuss your role.  You have such an extensive background and it was so interesting to listen to all you've done in your career.  And who would've known you live the next town over from me.  Good Luck with your acting debut!\n\n157#Accelerating into 2020|What a year of surprises! Thanks to each of you for bringing your insights, ideas, and energy to bear on our top 5 accounts. We've been meeting quarterly to review from every angle how we can from every perspective, impact the business. So many great ideas were uncovered and put into action immediately from these conversations. And each of us, learned something big about how with some focus, we could more directly impact big opportunities as an organization. Thank you for early and late meetings, for staying focused, and for caring so much about excellence! This has been an incredible 'test' of the WH network! Bravo!\n\n158#A True Global Content Team for Executive Forums|I wanted to commend all of you for your teamwork and diligence chronicling the key insights and learnings from the executive forums in the fall.  These insights are an important element for our ability to continue our thought leadership and communication touch-points with this high level audience. It will also help us internally - to ensure we - as a collective team - are out in front of emerging HR and people trends. Special shout-out to Sarah for the writing of the whitepaper (the final version which is coming soon!) and Dan for his foresight and strategy behind the people coverage of the forums, ensuring each one had a content lead to roll-up into the whitepaper output.\n\n159#Thanks to the data nerds|Thank you to everyone on this award for taking time to review questions and provide input for the upcoming full-time U.S. employee survey. What started out as a \"mini\" survey outside of the annual international survey has turned into quite a robust assessment of the employee experience in the U.S. We're tackling some sensitive issues such as harassment and discrimination and I really appreciate the thought each of you put into additional questions and answer options and getting the wording just right. I'm looking forward to seeing the results come in and using this data to build a compelling report that will drive leads and media inquires.\n\n160#Team creativity|Thank you for your help collecting and sharing insightful, relevant information for our Q4 customer acceleration meetings.  With your contributions, we were able to identify marketing opportunities and generate new ideas for delivering value to these important accounts.  Looking forward to continued collaboration and the wealth of innovative ideas that will result!\n\n161#The Details Matter|As we continue to modernize and leverage Social Selling in all facets of our business, new requirements and needs present themselves. With several new associates joining the organization it became clear that we needed some great new backgrounds and imagery that would align them with WH, our culture, and our branding. Dan I reached out to understand where I should go with my ask, and without hesitation you jumped in, reached out to Carrie, and got the project under way. Carrie, without skipping a beat, you rolled up your sleeves and created some beautiful graphics and images that align our people to WH and to our culture. I was blown away at your urgency and your pace. Thank you so much for making this a priority and executing flawlessly. I am grateful.\n\n162#New Thought Leadership, booked!|Dan and Kevin, today is an important day as we submit our latest thinking and thought leadership in the form of a draft new book to Mc Graw Hill!  Wow!  A world class publisher will today accept the work and experience of the collective Workhuman team and all our collective work and excellence.  It‚Äôs thank to you both for your project leadership, eagle eye editing and constant stewardship of this that we are here at this point today.  Thank you both sincerely from me and Eric, this a tremendous achievement that will within months provide great dividends. Well done!\n\n163#Content Suggestions|Sarah and Dan, I want to thank you for the sense of urgency in which you're both working to help the field sales team deliver impactful content to our prospective buyers.  I came to you a few weeks back with 2 suggestions - a cost of doing nothing piece and one around the potential need for organizations to report on their human capital investments.  Within a few hours you were mobilizing a way to make it happen.  We've created 1 piece and based on the conversation it started it is now being strategized as part of a larger campaign.  Thank you for always being willing to listen to my ideas (as half-baked as they normally are) and for working with a sense of urgency we need to reach our audience in a timely fashion!\n\n164#Capturing the Citizens Story|Dan, Thank you for your leadership and support around capturing the Citizens story. You are the #1 supporter of our customer stories - always reminding us that this validation content is gold. I appreciate you being there throughout the process - checking in, reviewing content (quotes within and outside of the final asset), and offering your help along the way. Thank you and I look forward to working with you on more of these opportunities in the future.\n\n165#Bringing the Humanity at HR Tech|Dan, Amy, Mike, and Max - Wonderful work at the HR Tech conference in Las Vegas. Shows like this are an incredible opportunity to influence the market - through key influencers, analysts, customers, and more.  There are countless items that play into the strategy - from social presence to meetings to sessions to dinners to drinks to content. It's a constant flurry of activities that show who we are as a company and people. Thank you for the passion you brought, the eagerness to learn and make new connections, and all the great relationship building along the way!\n\n166#Marketing Team Alignment|Dan, you are in inspiration for this newbie! You were proactive in gathering marketing director team input and helping to smooth over a challenging time of organizational change. The format was appropriate and the organization was on point.\n\n167#It's Planning Time!|Team! I wanted to send a huge thank you for the time and energy put into Q4 planning. Collaborating with this fine group of humans is always a pleasure. We have continued to refine the process, bring in more folks and I think each time we do this, we have a better end result! Kicking this off will be exciting and I think come 2020, we will evolve our thinking even more. Well done all!\n\n168#Start Spreading the Executive News|Thank you for all of your hard work in writing, designing, developing, and launching our first Executive Forum Newsletter. This addition of content to the Executive Program covered the theme of trust and this team is one I trust in - to get the project done and done well! From dotting i's and crossing t's in the content, to a branded design for this audience; from the development of new blog post links to cross referencing recipient lists in Salesforce; to reporting on the send via Marketo with a phenomenal open and click through rate - your efforts helped us achieve and measure success for what will continue to be a key communication initiative for the executive audience.\n\n169#Now that, is Acceleration!|Kristen and Dan, wanted to thank you both one, for letting me into the Acceleration account meeting party and two for being such amazing champions for the customer! You both took the time to dig into each account using all sorts of tools. You also took that information and synthesised it not into just a readout, but lots of good insight with some actionable next steps that can be taken now, but also to set us up for a bright future with our key customers. The hard work and preparation showed in the last 2 weeks of meetings. Well done and excited to see this all put into action!\n\n170#Q3 Acceleration|Thanks to this team for another outstanding Acceleration Project quarterly mind meld. Every quarter we come together representing the expertise and perspective of many areas of the business. This quarter was special as we've 'accelerated' our thinking and really got the team thinking bigger and making connections and recommendations. This commitment and intense work for our top 5 customers is paying off as we have come away with a laundry list of opportunities and ideas to grow and protect the business. Thank you for your teamwork, intense listening skills, and outstanding impactful insights!!!\n\n171#Steady Leadership|Dan - I am grateful for your continued leadership over the past few months. There have been countless examples of you of stepping up for time sensitive projects, helping guide team members during times of change, or you simply just asking the right questions on how you can help keep us on track.  You do all of this with a ton of projects on your plate. As we embark on our next phase of growth, it's reassuring to have you on the team. Your steadiness does not go unnoticed and is appreciated by so many members of the marketing team ‚Äì and outside marketing as well.  Thank you for your consistent dedication and focus to helping the company succeed.\n\n172#It Takes a Village...|Thank you all so much for your time and energy reviewing speaker applications for Workhuman Live 2020. We received hundreds of submissions and recommendations that needed to be properly vetted in a short period of time. You provided important background information on a lot of these applicants and evaluated each one based on our top criteria. The goal for next year‚Äôs speaker line-up is to present the world‚Äôs top business thinkers who are truly shaping the future of the workplace landscape. It‚Äôs a tricky balance to ensure we have renowned thought-leaders in the space while also bringing to light a few hidden gems that our audience can learn from. Each of you brought your experience, expertise, and unique perspectives to our group discussion on Monday. I love being around teammates who are just as excited as I am about this whole process. We‚Äôre just getting started but your insights have put us on the right path. Thanks all!\n\n173#Content is King, really, it is!|Dan and Sarah - what can I say, you are both amazing partners, but specifically in Q3, you have been lifesavers. Being short handed in demand, Sarah you have stepped in to provide some much needed to support to track content from creation to completion. I cannot tell you how much I appreciate that support. Dan, you are always willing to listen, checking in to see if we need anything at all. I have lost track how many times you have asked 'how can I help?'  I am so thankful for the continued partnership and teamwork. Cannot wait to see what Q4 brings!\n\n174#Commitment to Quality|Dan, thank you so much for your supportive leadership over many weeks as we‚Äôve worked to get multiple video projects across the finish line. I appreciate your interest in these projects, your consistent commitment to quality, and your willingness to work together to move roadblocks along the way. Thanks for always asking, ‚Äúwhat can I do to help?‚Äù Even if things feel out of our hands, it‚Äôs nice to know I have your support and I am always confident we will turn around a quality product in time. Thank you.\n\n175#Taking it to the next level|Team- Thank you so much for meeting with me yesterday to discuss taking Jesse‚Äôs book to the next level and brainstorming all things analytics with me. Sales will be ecstatic to have this campaign and I‚Äôm looking forward to the results pouring in!!\n\n176#Relationship building and more at SHRM 19|Great job at SHRM Annual Conference this week!  This conference is a great relationship building opportunity ‚Äì for us to continue to leverage the relationships we have and make new ones.  All with the intent of creating new business and thought leadership opportunities.  Mike ‚Äì excellent work with the SHRM Foundation.  This year‚Äôs format was different than past years ‚Äì but it remained a great way to connect with industry leaders and show Workhuman as a brand that cares. And the dinner with Cy Wakeman was amazing fun!  Dan ‚Äì great job in leveraging the show to get competitive intel, industry information to help our content strategy and new ideas to help our future messaging. Amy ‚Äì this was your first SHRM conference but you jumped right in!  You spent time at the booth, got some great media interviews and made new connections for Workhuman. Can't wait to see what comes of all of them. Well done all!\n\n177#What a Brainstorm|There‚Äôs nothing like a three-hour meeting, sandwiched between the company meeting, a marketing vp meeting, and countless other commitments.  Yet, every one of you came with your A-Game ‚Äì ready to brainstorm a whole new approach to the Workhuman Live website experience.  Thank you all for showing up focused, open-minded, and collectively in alignment on exceeding our audiences‚Äô expectations through the site.  Reimagining a website is never easy, especially when trying to set aside what we already know to try new things.  Every one of you stepped up to share your areas of expertise and add value into the overall plan.  Your input was so valuable and is helping to frame out an exceptional site plan for 2020.\n\n178#Dan the Man!|Great way to start the morning, Dan! Today you brought key stakeholders together to discuss what makes healthcare tick...not just healthcare but what seems to be looking like pharma, bio pharma, assisted living etc lol. Thank you for taking the time to schedule time on all of our busy calendars and recruit not 1 or 2 but 5 different business units to discuss all aspects of the industry. I left feeling like I wanted more, but still was able to get my regular job done;) Scratching the surface is what you called it...either way it was a great way to open up communication this am. Thanks again!!\n\n179#Because you care|Dan- I cant thank you enough for your continued efforts to learn the most efficient ways to use Workfront. You saw Dianne‚Äôs message about keeping tasks up to date so we can accurately report back to VP‚Äôs and immediately reached out to Traffic to check in and make sure you were doing your part. You‚Äôre not only paying attention, but you care and that means the world to us. Thank you! (I hope you‚Äôre also enjoying the new dashboard!)\n\n180#Let's talk data!|Thank you all for participating in this morning's data think tank (especially on a Friday before the long weekend!). This was an important first step in working collaboratively to unlock the power of the data each of us collect with our teams across Marketing. I was truly inspired by all of your ideas and perspectives, and there is so much potential for us to use these analytics to take the right actions to bring everything we do for Workhuman to the next level!\n\n181#Thank you for the support|These days we are so busy.  Our time is so valuable.  You spent 30 minutes with this new guy.  Listening to questions you probably heard 100 times over and answered with grace and clarity.  Thank you for teaching me how valuable teamwork is here at Workhuman and making this a welcoming environment.   I know from past experiences this is not the norm!  Thank you and I can't wait to take up more of your time in the future.\n\n182#Program Content Masters!|Team, thanks so much for taking a big chunk out of a very busy week to discuss content for demand programs in Q3. I loved the collaborative nature of the meeting. It was so productive; fueling our creative juices from the offsite gave us even more steam! I am psyched about the outcome and thrilled  we continue to elevate our partnership to get awesome content in front of our key decision makers! Laura, thank you for keeping on top of program timing and initiating this conversation to keep us all ahead o the calendar. Dan and Sarah, thanks for bringing your A-game, being so open-minded and having the goals top of mind. Go team!!!!\n\n183#Sometimes little things are big things :)|Hey Dan, I wanted to call you out for taking the time to scribe all the notes from our Marketing Leadership meeting last week. I've been out sick all week, and reviewing my notes etc - and was so happy to see how you've collected it all. I know its a little thing, but was super valuable to have it done and communicated. Thanks!\n\n184#Rebranded + new collateral to share with the world|Team - Since the start of the rebrand and even up until now, it‚Äôs been impressive to see how many content pieces you have played a part in updating, creating, and versioning! Between the rebrand for collateral and core campaigns the rough math in my head comes out to about 60 pieces!! You have each contributed so much time and effort to keep these on time and on brand. Thank you for all of your hard work! Sales is now well equipped to share Workhuman collateral with the world. Look out world!\n\n185#Making Time to Brainstorm|Dan, Lauren, Jen, and Geoff, thanks so much for your time during our call for speakers brainstorming session. It's helpful to hear new and exciting ideas on how we can update the call for speakers webpage. The design layout plays a huge role in how an applicant  absorbs who we are and what we're looking for. The text on the page needs to match the voice and tone of Workhuman while still being practical and instructional. We're on our way to creating a new template that serves all of these needs. I'm looking forward to seeing how it turns out!\n\n186#Supportive Leadership|This is an overdue thank you for your supportive leadership, especially as it relates to all of the work we all do around capturing customer stories. This is a sweet spot that I know you're super passionate about - and I can see that in the support you've provided me time and again around this work. Thanks for always reminding me of the value that this validation content provides. It's not always a quick turnaround on this kind of content. It takes careful planning, a lot of collaboration and it's easy to get bogged down in process and approvals, but the impact is worth the effort. I'm grateful to have you in my corner as we continue to evolve this work. Thank you!\n\n187#I see you...|Often, we look for singular moments or projects as a reason to share gratitude. But recently, I heard someone talk about how powerful it is to reach out to colleagues every now and again, to say: \"I see you.\" Especially when the pressures of our normal work are accumulating. I immediately thought of you. The past few months have been a huge challenge for the rebrand and the Workhuman event. Whether its adjusting the text on collateral pieces, helping rewrite bullet points on posters and event spaces, churning out headlines, emails, landing pages, white papers, working to keep the sales team informed of whats available (oh, and helping write a book?)... and I'm sure plenty more things that I'm not privy to. I just want you to know that I see you, and all your hard work and effort. You're a great partner.\n\n188#We will no longer be Dublin's best kept secret!|From Maureen and I squeezing an hour to brainstorm as quick as we could at Workhuman live, to the million emails requesting a change here and there, I cannot stress how proud I am with the finished product. As I was setting up tonight at Dublin Tech Summit, OUR STAND was the one companies like Apple were taking a picture of for ideas for future events!! Thank you all for your hard work, creativity and patience.  I truly believe after DTS, we will no longer be Dublin's best kept secret, but well on our way to being a sought after employer in the Dublin market.\n\n189#Wharton Wonder Team|I am grateful to you for your help at Workhuman with the Wharton research project. Doing a live research project was a first for the company - an opportunity that came about because of Workhuman itself. For us to continue to change the workplace and the work, we need to try new things and stretch ourselves. Each of you did a great job setting up to help at the event with the live study. Special kudos to Jesse and Greg for their involvement and expertise from the start and Lauren who managed all of it with the lead researcher - not an easy task with so many elements happening during the same timeframe.  Look forward to what the results will bring!\n\n190#Persona Workshop Warriors Unite!|I have such a grateful heart for this day, this entire team of Marketing mavens, and all the opportunities that sit within our reach. I have never felt more connected to our team than I do at this very moment. We just completed an all hands, all day persona workshop! Woohoo!!! Thank you for your investment. Thank you for being a kind audience that stayed engaged. Thank you for asking thoughtful questions. Thank you for your humor and your patience. Thank you for being real. Thank you for embracing the 7 1/2 hour marathon persona training session we shared today with gusto and heart! I truly believe that we will be a better team, and we will produce better marketing because of the time we spent together today. I can‚Äôt wait to hear your feedback about the agenda, the learning modules, the wiki‚Ä¶.ALL the things! I can‚Äôt wait to apply this first body of persona work to our marketing efforts. Let‚Äôs GOOOOOOO!\n\n191#Gratitudes for our breakout group leaders|Thank you for stepping up to lead the practice area breakout groups today. It was a packed agenda that I tried to choreograph down to the last minute and last detail. I felt completely at ease with the five practice area team presentations because I knew I had awesome leaders guiding the way. The teams were cross functional spanning all areas of our department including some new faces from our PR firm, but in watching everyone interact with each other, you would have thought we worked really closely together for decades. So much collaboration and lively discussion. Insightful presentations....It was a beautiful thing. Thanks again for your leadership.\n\n192#Utilizing Ambassadors to the fullest!|A huge thanks to each one of you for being amazing partners in really pushing our Ambassador strategy forward this year. This team is so supportive, responsive, positive and it feels like anything is possible when I work with you. Together we were able to carve out a new strategic plan to utilize all 35 of our Ambassadors and across a wide variety of activities (case studies, testimonials, videos, radio, blogs and more!). While we are still working to total up the outcomes, I know that what each of you owned and executed will be crucial to our future success. We are locked and loaded with brand new material, voices, opinions that will super charge our \"WorkHuman Voice\" to so many others. If Ambassadors did not participate this year, they are eager to be a part of even more throughout the year. I heard such nice feedback from this group about how kind, smart and fun our people are and that they loved being a part of these areas. Thank you for all of your hard work and for truly putting customers first. You are a part of what makes these folks ambassadors for life. :)\n\n193#GF -> WH|I am so grateful for all you did to launch the rebranded website. It took a long way to get there but wow, we all did it! The end result is clean, bright and engaging and one URL!! The words are crisp and the IA is looking great. There were so many parts and pieces that it would be like an Emmy speech (cue the bassoons dragging me off stage!) thanking each and every one of you but I am sure you all know how much you contributed to the success. A few highlights: Angela, being the mad trafficker she is, Matt D, behind the scenes supporting and guiding, Maggie, Lauren and Dan's killer copy skills, rocking the new messaging! Geoff, the midnight coder, always pushing to try to break the chains that are Connelly! Jay and Ty, your collaborative designs and dividing and conquering with a smile, and onsite Nashville, Anthony and Brian coding some last minute styles so pages looked great! Lastly, Brian's first big launch as a leader on the team and what a great job! Here's to many more.\n\n194#Mega/Super Session Flip|Thank you all so much for stepping up and taking some shifts for the Mega/Super Session flips! We needed these last min and you all took some time out of your days and responsibilities to help usher in the General Session room!!! Thank you so much for lending a hand and helping out!!\n\n195#Comms & Content Mastery at Workhuman Live|Wow. This team rocked Workhuman Live. It is truly an immersive adventure - with hard work and focus leading to \"our water\" - an incredible experience that will empower and enrich our leaders. On the content side, Dan - incredible leadership. You support and lift your team when they need it most - and spearhead so many other initiatives, particularly the post-show content strategy. Lauren C - words cannot fully describe your enormous impact on the event in managing our speakers and tracks. So many details - you get it done with poise, class, and determination. Sarah - your efforts leading our blog strategy has resulted in another step up for our on-site thought leadership. The bar has risen again! Lauren B - your creative approach continually up-levels the words that our attendees see throughout. And at the event, you were a huge part of the blogging efforts. Aaron and Lynne - fantastic job blogging at the conference, finding the right insights to help our attendees take back key learnings to help their organizations grow. Jess - while you were not able to join us at the event, you were invaluable leading up supporting so many writing needs (and your editing skills rock too!). For internal comms, Colleen - fantastic work leading our strategy this year, helping our company \"feel\" the event better than ever. Kristen - your creativity & determination brought it to life internally, plus your support on social was huge! Clare - loved your timely updates and great ideas. Your idea to ask Kat for an internal video was genius! For external comms, Mike - masterful job with our influencer community once again. Their engagement was incredible! 20 interviews including some of our keynotes with Workhuman Radio (your baby). Just amazing! And Amy, while you couldn't be there, your impact on our PR coverage was huge with some fantastic pieces and more to come. Thank you to the best comms and content team the event world has ever seen. Grateful for all of you.\n\n196#Driving Miss Crazy.|Dan, I want to thank you for being the consummate gentleman and offering me and my ‚Äúlogistical anxiety‚Äù a ride to and from the airport for the second Workhuman year in a row (even after last year I played that April Fool‚Äôs joke on you). I don‚Äôt know what other manager I‚Äôll ever have who‚Äôll show up to my house with the soundtrack to Les Miserables already playing for his former theater geek of an employee - probably none because you‚Äôre one of a kind and I really appreciate your generosity. And sorry I pranked you again (and you fell for it again). Next year, I‚Äôll drive!\n\n197#More web game than Spiderman|Team it has been an exciting past few months working though the changes, enhancements and additions to the Workhuman corporate website. Innovation, Imagination and Determination sum up the weekly sprints, days and nights of hard work that went into making it happen. Tyler, Jay and Jess your designs are full of life and energy. Between the rebrand and Workhuman for teams, so much great creative was produced  in a short amount of time. Dan and Lauren great work on creating and reviewing all the new content. Brian great work on managing the project and daily sprints as well as  jumping into code to work on Development. Matt thank you for working with us on the domain changes and redirects. Angela thank you for keeping things on schedule and organized in Workfront. Grateful for and proud of this team for what we have accomplished!\n\n198#Internal Live Blog Team|Another year, another crazy few days documenting all the great content at Workhuman Live. I want to express my gratitude to you - our internal live blog team - for your critical role in producing 9 live blogs covering keynotes, panels, and Q&A sessions in Nashville. This required quick writing (Lauren, Lynne, and Dan!), quick editing (thanks for double checking with eagle eyes Lauren & Dan!), and an eye for compelling stories and stats that will fuel post-conference content for the next few months (Lauren, Lynne, and Aaron!). Brian - I also appreciate your fast turnaround for getting these blogs on the Workhuman Live website, giving visitors and potential 2020 attendees a taste of what the event is all about. Already seeing some great traction on social with these posts. Thank you!\n\n199#Leading Human|Dan, in the midst of all the projects we are juggling right now - from re-brand phase 2, to Workhuman Live, follow up plans, and more - I wanted to send a quick note of gratitude for the way in which you \"lead human.\" This manifests itself in the way you trust your team to get the work done (whenever and however it is most efficient), but also make yourself available if we have questions. You're also not afraid to get your hands dirty and help share the load as work volume increases. And finally, I appreciate the way you lead with positivity and just focus on the most effective way to get the work done. By leading human, we can achieve anything as a team. Thank you!\n\n200#There's life after Nashville?|Dan, Jill, and Laura - While everyone is heads down preparing for Nashville, you are working hard on what looks like a kick-ass follow-up plan! Thank you for taking me (and  many others) through it over the last week to talk through 'all the things' - How does this impact Workhuman Cloud for Teams? How should sales and CS follow-up? What's the ABM strategy? Is the timing aggressive enough? Will this plan help progress opps?  It's shaping up beautifully with quite a few \"new and improved\" elements over previous years that will be exciting to test and see how attendees respond. Thank you for bringing a fresh, smart perspective to this important, time-sensitive initiative!\n\n201#The Great Communicators of Workhuman|I am grateful for your collective amazing work on the brand evolution in the past couple of weeks. Each of you stepped up in different, very important ways to ensure we announced it to the wider world (and internally) in an effective, meaningful way. There were twists, turns, changes - but you rolled with it and focused on the larger objective. And of course, as big projects tend to do, the time needed to get everything done crept into evening hours (and sometimes early morning hours given our global needs). And yet, you were all undaunted and got it the timing and the messaging right.  Well done team!\n\n202#Acceleration Kickoff Team|A big thank you and much gratitude to the entire team involved in kicking off our global internal 'review' of our top 5 customers! It took many hours of prep to do the research, thinking, and reporting for each of your areas of expertise AND then several more hours to come together as a team and review all of the great insights.  Thank you for digging in, thinking BIG, and committing yourselves to this important effort. One more review meeting to go! With every call we've made some connections, identified some opportunities, and put ourselves in a better place strategically.  Great work!\n\n203#Becoming Workhuman - Phase I achievement unlocked!|Team, I hope each and every one of you has taken a moment this week to appreciate what you have achieved. With ZERO external support (except for a couple of contractors doing \"find and replace\" logo updates, but 