moving, all so important to drive our business forward. Cheers to more amazing teamwork ahead!\n\n207#Dedication to Team Development|Dan - Thank you for all of your leadership with employee development conversations with your team. This is so critical toward building a great team. It is so important to put the time into this - and to be thoughtful and considerate. You have done both and also partnered with HR to ensure they have intimate knowledge for the great talent we need to cultivate. And to our talent, to making sure they feel supported and cared for as they continue to grow, learn, and develop their careers at the company.\n\n208#MLK Day Message|Team, thanks for moving quickly to help create the MLK Day video message commemorating today's holiday and its meaning in 2019. Building a media company within marketing starts with projects like this where we align with news and events that match our company values. That is certainly true of MLK Day, which celebrates a man who was a constant voice of humanity, compassion, and nonviolence. Dan, thanks for putting this idea out there in the original 2019 content calendar - excellent planning! Daisy, thanks for working quickly to block off Steve's calendar. Colleen, I appreciate your last-minute help in putting the internal message together so we could keep employees informed. Matt and James, thanks for being open to this idea and bringing your A-game to create a high-quality video that gets our message across. And finally Steve, thanks for stepping up to share this important message, and teaching me something new about how Dr. King's \"I have a dream\" speech unfolded that day in 1963. Looking forward to working with this team on more projects like this in 2019!\n\n209#Reviews in record time|Dan, there were some quick turnarounds today where I asked for your speedy review. Thanks so much for getting eyes on them so quickly. I really appreciate it, and the fact that I can always count on you!\n\n210#Connecting on Conversations Stories|Dan - I am so excited by the new case studies coming. The first - already approved and out to sales - was Qlik. And the second - coming soon - will be first First Tech.  Both of these started to develop from the HR Tech conference (and the panel), where you had such determination to pursue these new stories and build the relationships with our customers. Thank you for your leadership and tenacity. These stories are critical to helping us sell the recognition-performance story and connection. Thank you for all of your awesome work!\n\n211#Thoughtful cross-functional e-comm participation!|Thanks to this group for your attendance at the e-commerce quarterly meeting and for contributing your thought-provoking questions and ideas!  It is fantastic to have such engagement from partners across the organization and to see the buy-in you all have to our plan and progress.  It means a lot to the whole e-commerce team to see this level of commitment to everything we're doing, and you all brought up some excellent ideas that we will be taking on and exploring further.  Thanks for dedicating your time - please join us next time and spread the word!\n\n212#Human Assets|Dan and Sarah, I can't thank you enough for all the incredible work you've done to make all of our assets easier to find, up to date, and organized. Maybe you knew it needed to be done, or maybe you were just sick of hearing sales complain about it and you wanted to quiet us down :)  But whatever the reason, I've been able to find new, up to date, and very informative assets quicker than ever before via Sharepoint and Postwire. It's been monumental, especially lately, because I'm trying to utilize all the great work that Jesse and his team are doing by presenting these awesome new whitepapers, data sheets, science, studies, recorded Webinars, videos etc. to make compelling reasons for prospects to talk to me/us. And more than ever, I've found everything easy to find in an organized and central location in either Sharepoint or Postwire. And also, both of you have been quick and spot on with helping me recently on \"one offs\" when I told you what I needed and you created it or fixed something outdated for current use. You may deal with or create our assets, but you truly ARE the assets that keep Globoforce going!\n\n213#Rockin' the Rapid Response|All - awesome work with the recent rapid response video, blog, internal, and social post for Steve's response to the recent shootings.  This was a great example of how we can respond in an agile way to news that hits home - and aligns with our vision to make work more human.  In our work, we help millions of people around the world. What we do matters. Making people feel respected, empowered, and appreciated is helping make the world a better place. There are so many things that happen in our world that run counter to who we are as a company.  By giving our point of view and reflecting on how the commonalities of people (particularly in the workplace) are an opportunity for progress, we are helping advance the conversation.  Thank you all for your passion and enthusiasm.  And of course Steve, thank you for being that type of leader who truly cares and delivering that message so incredibly well!\n\n214#feMENism|I want to take a moment and give a big shout out to all the men who attended last week's first-ever-hosted Globoforce Women's Network event. Whether you were there as an attendee, a panelist, or just there to help live-stream our message to the world, your presence mattered. I'm a scream-it-from-the-rooftops feminist but I know that even if 100% of women stood up for our equality it would never be enough‚Äìwe need you to stand up too. This isn't a social statement, just one of simple math: 100% of humans need to believe in equality for it to be true in practice. I've heard some men saying that they haven't joined the GFWN because they don't know what they can do. But it isn't about doing. It's just about showing up, witnessing, and supporting. You did all of those things ‚Äì¬†and it matters. Thank you.\n\n215#Content Calendar - Building the Future!|Team ‚Äì You all did a wonderful job on the content/editorial calendar for 2019.  This is a new approach for us (and mindset shift toward our customer/user) ‚Äì using our thought leadership and content as a foundational element for our marketing plan. Each of you were thoughtful, collaborative, and looked at the big picture.  The final product will greatly help align our outward-facing message ‚Äì and make us a truly formidable marketing engine.  Thank you for all of your work and enthusiasm!  I can‚Äôt wait for 2019 and the future.  Kevin\n\n216#Sounding Board|Dan, I want to take second to thank you for being such a wonderful sounding board. Every week in our one-one-one meeting you start by asking me how I‚Äôm doing and if you can help make anything easier. Then I proceed to talk for 25-minutes straight and ask for advice on a hundred different things. You‚Äôre a great listener and always have a suggestion that comes from positive and supportive place. I appreciate the time you take to check-in during the week.\n\n217#One small courtesy!|Your one small courtesy is causing a ripple effect and I wanted to thank you. You don't know this but I am coordinating 11 deep dive sessions with 12 different departments, 21 individuals and 3 time zones! Holy moly! I wanted to put in a request for a temporary EA to help me haha! I was so close to the finish line and came upon a blockage. Because you are so considerate, you didnt hesitate when I contacted you to rearrange time and space with your team to make way for my need. A small courtesy BUT a big impact. Thank you for always being the kindest!!\n\n218#Marketing Leadership at Work!|Big Team - thank you for all the hard work and homework you put into preparing for the Marketing Offsite. It took weeks of prep, but we plowed through the entire organizational plan AND gave ourselves space for