 a great teammate like you to get the job done right. Thank you!\n\n222#It takes a village of humans ?|Thank you team WorkHuman for your dedication, sense of urgency, and partnership on the agenda announcement last week. Dianne as always you kept the project moving and made sure we covered all the details up front and when we had last minute changes/edits. Lauren - you are so agile and easy to work with on the many, many, many different copy reqs and I am really happy with how everything came together thanks to your quick responses and thinking on your feet. Dan - thank you for being right there with us and making sure we get approvals on all the copy as well. Sarah - Your blog announcement was spot-on and will be a great piece for us to repurpose in social for the next few weeks as well as on the website! Speaking of website, Brian, thank you for being on top of all things workhuman.com and keeping us abreast of the metrics, goals, and sprints each week and especially as they relate to this campaign. Mike - you are a rock star, simply put! I know that last minute-edits to an email email after it is already in Marketo is not always the easiest ask but, you took that in with a sense of humor and made the finished product look and feel great. Pam - With all you have going on you were able to take time on Thursday morning to be the \"executive approver\" and make sure we got the email out by lunch time while I was working from home and not feeling great, I am so grateful for you! Finally, Jay and James - thank you both for helping to conceptualize and create a truly unique and engaging motion graphic video announcement for social! This was the ask that really could have used more time but, we knew what we had to do and you both took it in stride, and produced a really amazing video that is already seeing high engagement rates on social. THANKS TEAM! ‚úîÔ∏è\n\n223#The dynamic 19 collaborators!|You're all \"good apples\" in my eye! Thank you to each of you for your help putting together the September Globonews content. The newsletter is no small effort and this past month there were 19 involved from all areas of the company to share information about all that's happening in Globoforce. Thank you for sharing your events, news, helping craft the messaging, and making it look great. Once again, so appreciative of the partnership I find every month when I reach out. Thank you!\n\n224#Customer Networking|Dan - Thank you for using your trip to HR Tech in Vegas to help build important relationships with our Conversations customers. You understand how important it is that we get some early case studies into the market and were quick to reach out post-event, make the ask, and introduce me to get the ball rolling. You even managed to get Vicki from Qlik to write out answers AND conduct a phone interview. Between this content and the panel transcript, I had 15 pages of quotes to work from for the case study. Better to have too much information than not enough! Thanks to your legwork, I have an initial draft of the piece which will (fingers-crossed) turn into a valuable marketing and sales resource. Thanks for your quick teamwork and initiative on this!\n\n225#Customer Marketing Plan Mavens!|Extended Customer Marketing team ‚Äì this is a bit (ok, A LOT) tardy, but genuine nevertheless. We joined forces and pulled together a marketing plan several weeks ago to document what each of our respective teams were doing to help drive forth our marketing efforts to a very important audience ‚Äì our customers. Throughout the final months of the summer, we were in major planning mode and had just put forth our first group plan for Conversations Then directly on the heels of that, we asked you to do a similar plan for Customer Marketing. I appreciate each of your unique contributions. As to be expected with a dozen or so contributors, there were multiple rounds of Powerpoint slide reviews with changes ‚Äì some small, but some more complicated. We need more data, we need more details! We need more graphics! But wait, there's one more thing! No matter what I asked for, you were all committed and focused on getting the final deck to a good place. Now, with the plan approved, and many elements in motion, I‚Äôm sure you‚Äôre just as excited as I am to start seeing the results of all our work. I think I can speak for Pam, Stacey, Jill C, and Janet, when I say thank you, everybody! We couldn‚Äôt have pulled this off without you!\n\n226#My testimonial|A big thank you to everyone involved in getting the latest round of testimonials across the finish line. Kevin, you always take the time to review and ensure we‚Äôre putting our best foot forward ‚Äì you provide valuable insight and feedback along the way. Shweta, you did a ton of follow up to secure approvals from our customers, ensuring they felt comfortable and were happy with the final product. Dan, you ensured the new assets were accessible across all of our channels and communicated to our Sales/Marketing teams. Matt F and Jay, I love the look of this latest round. Thank you for combining old footage with new footage, and for making us look good! Angela, thanks for stepping up to ensure this project moved forward in my absence. Matt D, you‚Äôve done an incredible job with the resources page on workhuman.com ‚Äì thanks for ensuring our testimonials are featured so beautifully. I feel very lucky to work with colleagues I can count on!\n\n227#Rocking HR Tech|Fantastic work at HR Tech last week.  It was great to connect and work with you on so many elements and projects.  A few individual highlights:  Erik ‚Äì great job connecting with our customers on site.  What a fun dinner!  But beyond the dinner, you helped out in any way you could during the conference. Shweta ‚Äì amazing work getting that panel set and working with all the right parties to secure our customers.  It was an amazing session that will help us for months and years to come!  Mike ‚Äì your great relationship with Jason helped so much with the panel interest. Your work with influencers and connections with Microsoft during the show also go a long way!  Dan ‚Äì awesome job taking all the right nuggets from the conference and getting the market insights we need.  You‚Äôve also started the case study with our customers so we can build on from the panel to leverage for our Conversations marketing.  Well done all!\n\n228#Helping hands on HR Tech Handouts!|Thank you Stacey and Dan for your help getting Ro and Erik their handouts for HR Tech. It was a mad dash to get the product brief on Conversations to a \"print ready\" place by the time everyone was taking off for Las Vegas, and we ultimately had to find a place to print them onsite. Stacey - you didn't even hesitate when I was trying to figure out the most convenient way to get them printed and facilitated the entire online order. Dan, first you volunteered to travel with the printouts, and then when we found out we could have the order fulfilled in Vegas, you raised your hand to pick up the order for me and get them to Ro and Erik. I feel extremely lucky to work with awesome teammates like you two! Thanks again!\n\n229#Building the WorkHuman Agenda Puzzle|Team ‚Äì incredible work by all of you in building out the first phase of the WorkHuman agenda and speakers. This was a process that began soon after WorkHuman 2018 with a call for speakers, which resulted in more than 600 submissions to go through!  Each of you played a key role in researching these speakers, vetting their work and stage presence, and making recommendations. And when we came together to review, you were open, shared your views and opinions, and worked together.  Making and baking the WorkHuman content cake is a complicated puzzle ‚Äì all driven by the goal of building a world-class agenda that meets our business goals and aligns with our ambitious attendance targets.  Thank you for all of your efforts and enthusiasm.  Special thanks to Lauren for quarterbacking it all ‚Äì and ensuring that the management of the speakers is in great shape as we enter the prime marketing weeks and months.\n\n230#Courageous leadership at its best|Dan, there's a Simon Sinek quote that comes to mind when I think of you as a manager, \"A star wants to see himself rise to the top. A leader wants to see those around him become stars.\" I want to thank you for always empowering me to bring my best self to my work. It means so much to feel supported, listened to, and understood as I move forward in my role here. From taking our grammar show \"on the road\" to trusting me with all manner of projects, you truly are a courageous leader - always steadfast and calm, always letting others shine, and I sure appreciate you for this.\n\n231#Copy. Content. Careers.|A huge thank you for all of your amazing help writing copy, reviewing drafts, adding content, getting creative, and ensuring our Careers page is on brand, well written and enticing to candidates! There was a LOT to do - between the department pages and each individual section on the site - all the way through to selecting the headings! You were both incredibly helpful, supportive, patient and on-board. I appreciate the thought, time and energy that went into making sure our careers page really shined. You are a pleasure to work with and I'm absolutely thrilled with the result. Thank you!\n\n232#Website content masters|Thank you so much for your invaluable work on the content for the latest updates to globoforce.com.  From new Customer pages to Careers and Department pages, you delivered it all on time and with the highest quality.  It's very empowering to be part of such a high-performing team and I consider myself very lucky to work with you.\n\n233#A Second Set of Eyes - WorkHuman Regional Forums|Dan, thanks so much for your making yourself available last week to review the first draft of the WorkHuman Regional Forums presentation. You got back to me within 24-hours on any edits and suggestions. With multiple presentations being created for fall events, we're on a tight timeline and your quick and thorough insights helped to keep the project on track!\n\n234#4th and 1 yard to go|After our onsite with Nike, we didn't know where we stood. On Tuesday last week, they sent us another request. One that we saw as a positive as they had given us an opportunity to continue to position Globoforce and why we are the right partner. It was not an easy  task with 12 questions, that required very detailed responses, and 5...yes 5 references that the wanted in their hands by Thursday. So a whole 2 days to turn this around. When it's 4th down and a yard to go, it all comes down to execution. Executing on what the team needs to move the line and get that 1 yard to keep the game winning drive alive. Everybody stepped up, took creative approaches, did their job and just executed on what needed to be done. It was nothing short of inspiring! Thank you for the effort and energy you put into those 2 days.\n\n235#A focus on Conversations|While a number of important marketing initiatives have supported Conversations since launch, until recent weeks we haven't had the opportunity or the bandwidth to come together as a team with a cohesive plan to increase awareness, drive demand and better supports the sales and customer success teams. The plan we presented this week is a framework we can build on to better reach the market with a compelling message, and to communicate across marketing and with sales. The planning process got us moving and shines a light on where we need to focus. Thank you all for making the time to contribute with already very full schedules --  a special shout out to Eric B for shepherding the team to get this done!\n\n236#Fast as a speeding bullet point...|Dan and Lauren, You both were absolutely AWESOME in catering to the needs of our prospect.  It was a plea for PPT creativity and Content support for a big executive leadership pitch for Globoforce.  Even though we are already Vendor of Choice (VOC), we needed to present our best arguments specific to the organization.  GREAT work by both of you to respond in 36 hours and then follow up with edits after as well.  We find out soon  if we're a go.... Rog\n\n237#Team Nike|Dan, Thank you for jumping in last minute during a holiday week to help draft up scripts and talking points for our Nike videos. It was a busy week with many people on vacation and you stepped up to make sure it got completed quickly. Thank you for always being such a great teammate!\n\n238#It takes a village|Thank you to everyone who contributed to the submission of our IHAF awards this year. Each of you jumped in to contribute, providing project descriptions, design files, performance statistics, helping to track down old video links, and overall making sure we were putting our best foot forward. Holly, you spent extra time walking me through all the workhuman campaigns from 2017 and into 2018 so we could get a big picture view of what was working (and not working) which will in turn influence how we approach the creative moving into this year. Angela, you were my partner in crime for the whole project - contacting print vendors, managing timelines, and putting together the final shipped submission. Thanks to everyone for making this a full marketing team effort. I can't wait to see how it goes!\n\n239#Deal or No Deal|Thank you Dan, Angela, and Alana for helping me put together a presentation for a potential customer. With Globoforce as the recommended vendor we needed slides that could be presented to their ELT. Dan, thanks for taking the time to set up a call with the prospect to identify their needs before you headed off to bootcamp . Angela, as always you were patient and flexible moving the project along with a less than 24-hour deadline. Alana, you brought the PPT to life (love the puzzle slide) and the prospect was very impressed. Fingers crossed the deal is sealed soon.\n\n240#Copy that|Hey Dan! I want everyone to know how agile and helpful you have been this past week with some script advising for several video projects. Taking time out of your banana-ram schedule to fine tune a demo walkthrough script, as well as sitting down to interview Ben, both for the upcoming Nike RFP. You were calm, cool and collect as always. Also, I'm trying to learn and adopt the copy rules you set forth. Please don't hate me if I mess them up! As with every video project you have stepped in to help with, your work was fast and of the highest quality. Thanks for going the extra mile to collaborate with us. Can't wait for the next one!\n\n241#Talk about an agile and dedicated team player!|Dan, we can't thank you enough for jumping in to help us with the video shoot today. Not only did you provide the team with an invaluable framework of specific, yet conversational questions in record time, you also moved around important meetings to be our off-camera talent guiding the discussion. You nailed it. Your calm demeanor, agility, and team-first mentality is always very much appreciated when the pressure is on. This was the 2nd time you helped us in a pinch and just want to say thank you X 100!\n\n242#Last minute video scripts for Nike|Dan- thank you for joining our kickoff meeting for Nike last minute and being so willing to meet our very tight deadline to have scripts put together for some important videos that will address their pain points. Your deadline turned out to be even sooner than I originally anticipated as we decided in the meeting we need copy first thing after the holiday. I know this was most likely another thing added to your plate while teammates were on vacation and knowing you, you most likely worked on this on your holiday. It didn‚Äôt go unnoticed! Thank you for joining and contributing to help this huge Nike deal! Love your ‚Äújust do it‚Äù mentality.\n\n243#Ready for your close up!|In true Globoforce fashion, when I put the call out for photoshoot models, so many people jumped at the chance to help. A photoshoot like the one we held this week takes true teamwork and the work of many to be successful. I am truly appreciative for all of you who made time and were patient/flexible/available throughout the process. Thank you to those in scheduled shoots and for those I grabbed last minute who were willing to jump right in. The careers website is going to look AMAZING because of so many of you! We are going to have an incredible photo library of our incredible people doing incredible things. Thank you to all of you - I am truly grateful!\n\n244#Respect for Conversations Marketing|Team, you got it done! Thank you for your dedication to the Conversations marketing plan.  We had a tight deadline to from project start to check-in to executive review.  It was easy for each of you to deliver your information because you're so organized.  I appreciate your ability to turn around my requests quickly and provide the necessary detail to build the marketing team's Conversation marketing plan.  Thank you for your quick input and positive response to this project and for living our value of 'Respect for Urgency.'  Great job everyone.\n\n245#Thanks for the great start!|Dan, thank you for stepping up to introduce one of our most beloved WorkHuman speakers during the Framingham WorkHuman Wednesday. Your sharing of some of the behind the scenes fun details added to the moment. Thank you for starting off the session on such a fun note!\n\n246#Tackling the hard stuff|Dan, I wanted to say thank you for the time and effort you've put into the collateral updates thus far. Yes, I realize our work is not done, but I'd say we're very close to moving into the design phase for the product briefs for Conversations and Social Recognition, and as a result of our brainstorming, we have agreed upon a new approach for the WHC brochure which will make that a very valuable asset. With the launch of WHC, the way we need to talk about our solution has evolved so writing content for these new pieces is a challenge because there is so much overlap in terms of features and benefits. Of course, that's entirely by design and a good thing for our customers, but it hard not to be repetitive. I realize you are spread thin right now, but you never let that impact your attitude and positive approach nor the high quality of your work. I look forward to finalizing these important collateral pieces together. Thank you, again!\n\n247#Reverse interview team!|Thank you for being part of my interview team for the Recruiter opening! It's always interesting to wear the hat of hiring manager and sit in your seat and I greatly appreciate the time you took to prepare, interview and provide feedback for this critical role. I respect your opinion and value our recruiter/hiring manager relationship so much - thank you for stepping up and being MY interview team this time around. An interesting and very successful reversal!\n\n248#Sales Training|I wanted to send a thank you to the three of you for taking the time to prepare and deliver today's sales training session.  Being able to navigate and use the resources available is key to the success of the sales team.  Thanks for taking the time to deliver high quality collateral and helping us all learn how to access it.\n\n249#Team Oxford Comma|Thank you both so much for the content style reminders this morning in our marketing meeting. It's amazing how passionate we can get about abbreviations and sentence caps. I know it can feel like a small thing, but it has such a huge impact on our brand perception, so I appreciate you physically presenting this to make sure everyone understands the rules and why we make them. I can't wait for our next round of deep conversation around titles and how much I detest the a.m./p.m. treatment‚Äìthank you for carrying the consistency torch! (Please note that the title of this award is in title case!)\n\n250#Weaving Personal Story with Our Core Tenets|Dan, thank you for your contribution to the blog announcing the premiere of Steve's movie next week. Personal stories always perform best on the blog because they are relatable and human. You wrote a post that gives just enough history for those who don't know Steve's story, but also weaves in your own personal connection to Steve and ties in the themes of the movie to Globoforce's core tenants. I'm always looking to give our blog readers quality, compelling content that is true to Globoforce's human brand - and this post accomplished that. Thank you!\n\n251#Testimonial Teamwork|Kevin, Dan and Shweta, Thank you so much for your teamwork on the latest round of customer testimonials. You were all involved in the planning process leading up to WorkHuman. Dan and Shweta ‚Äì you made time in your schedules on-site to meet with the customers, put them at ease, answer questions, and ensure everything went smoothly with the interviews. Kevin ‚Äì I know you somehow managed to connect with as many customers as possible on site amid many competing priorities. Now you‚Äôve all teamed up to review the latest round and help to prep the videos for customer review/approval. I really appreciate the teamwork, and the time you‚Äôre taking on top of all of your other work to keep this moving forward. I know the videos, and our customers, are in great hands with this team. Much appreciated!\n\n252#Swooping in to assist!|Dan, I can't thank you enough for responding, with lightening speed, to my request for healthcare references and white papers when I was at a conference last week.  I ran into a CHRO at a prospective healthcare company.  We were at a breakfast meeting and I needed some information on the fly. I took a chance and sent a quick e-mail to you.  Sure enough, you responded immediately and it was so very helpful.  It was amazing.  Thank you!\n\n253#Nashville here we go!|A huge thank you to both of you for jumping in with input and direction for the new Nashville branding. Jen, we're totally on the same brainwave lately with all the new Nashville stuff, and you've been powerhousing and pushing out email after email and banner after banner to get this thing ready to show. Dan, we asked you for some direction on where WorkHuman is going this year in terms of content and you took the time to add mood words, a new mission statement, content tracks and more to our initial deck so we could get off and running. It has been absolutely awesome to see how the two of you approach all the different aspects of this event - I can't wait to see where Nashville ends up!\n\n254#WorkHuman Customer Testimonial Videos|I want to thank you for you making time in your schedule to assist me as a content expert with the customer testimonial shoots throughout WorkHuman. There are many plans to leverage these videos assets in campaigns and they will help immensely. With all of our crazy schedules, non-stop blogging, meetings here, parties there, adjusting your schedule to make sure we got the goods from these shoots was a huge help and the final product would not have been as great without you. Thank you.\n\n255#Resources for Resources|This is a bit overdue, but thank you all for the various critical roles you all played in getting our new online Resource Center launched.  When we kicked off, the vendor told us it was generally a 8-12 week launch period.  They hadn't met THIS marketing department yet!  From integrating with existing systems to troubleshooting forms to creating, organizing, and entering content, you all took this project to heart and helped get us online in 3 weeks!  It was truly a mad dash and you all pulled out all the stops.  Great work and thank you!\n\n256#Guest Blog Gratitude|I can't put into words how inspired I am after #WorkHuman last week. So many ideas flowing both personally and professionally (yes, this is really true and not just something we just say in our marketing!) Dan - thank you for embracing my idea to write about the parenthood themes I noticed and for your guidance while at WorkHuman. It was totally organic how I just came up to you in between keynote sessions, told you my idea, and walked away from our conversation with a plan on how I was going to frame the message and tie it back to life events and the human workplace.  Sarah - you're baaaaack! Your keen eye and editing skills were the extra sauce I really needed to put the finishing touches on the post, especially in spots where I was feeling stuck. Bottom line - thank you both so much for embracing this idea and for being amazing, collaborative teammates.\n\n257#Onsite Eagle Eyes|Dan, Holly and Lauren,   I can't thank you all enough for taking the time to review the onsite email communications for our attendees at this year's WorkHuman. You were all busy with your own tasks and sessions but still found time to make sure our attendees were receiving a quality message each morning. Whether it was an Oxford comma out of place ;) or session locations/times that needed to be updated, you all did a great job with the review. I have such confidence knowing that we have this team in place to catch any mistakes that may need to rectified. You all were AMAZING and I appreciate all the support. I look forward to working with each of you on the follow up to come!\n\n258#Comms and Content Dream Team|This team was nothing short of AMAZING for WH18.  Lauren C ‚Äì Flawless execution, unwavering determination, and smart work and management.  80+ speakers. You were absolutely dynamite at the event!  Dan ‚Äì great leadership throughout. No matter what content was needed for our campaign, you were there!  Amanda ‚Äì You had a big part in speaker selection, so many presentations, and customer testimonials. Shweta ‚Äì  a key role in selecting speakers as well as proposals for keynotes. And who can forget the  perseverance in you getting Simon Sinek! There was media at the event plus customer testimonials. Lauren B ‚Äì you infused a new energy into our WH copy and content. Creative, fun, lively.  Your words knit together an on-site narrative that flowed beautifully.  Sarah P ‚Äì  You played a huge part in those speaker selections last year.  Who can forget there were 500+ submissions as well your idea to segment tracks by HR audience. Colleen ‚Äì phenomenal internal communications leading up to the event ‚Äì ensuring everyone had everything they needed.  You also gave our charities an experience they won‚Äôt ever forget! Kristen ‚Äì sharing the WH experience with our employees. You also managed our WorkHuman fellows, giving them a week they will remember forever.  Aaron ‚Äì so many writing hats in the lead up to and at WH ‚Äì to support current and future follow-up.  Emily ‚Äì so many great blog posts in the lead up to WH. And on site, you took control like you were running a newsroom!  You made it look easy.  Mike ‚Äì 30+ influencers, 200 registrations (an incredible 4x increase). Also leading our social efforts, plus WH radio ‚Äì with 23 interviews onsite!  The work and accomplishments of this team is incredible. It‚Äôs also the caring, and collaboration. Helping each other when needed and fillings gaps when seen.  I know we will continue to hear about more hidden heroics from this group in days ahead.\n\n259#WorkHuman.com All-Star Team|Thank you all for making WorkHuman.com a success all conference long! Over the course of 4 days we launched 5 separate versions of the site, each with up to date content showcasing the very best of WorkHuman. From our initial strategy meetings weeks ago to the launch of the 2019 Nashville announcement yesterday you have all been amazing teammates who have gone above and beyond to make sure WorkHuman.com and all of its content is a worthy extension of the WorkHuman brand. We're on to 2019!\n\n260#No rest for the weary!|Dan, on our way back from dinner tonight, I mentioned that I‚Äôd love another set of eyes on the press releases before I set them up on the Wire. You had just finished telling me 