m put employees first and I am certain they will be appreciative! Thanks for including employees in this one-in-a-WorkHuman opportunity.\n\n264#MnG Masters|I wanted to thank you both for the urgent and quick help getting a few Meet n Greets setup and changed. Your quick (almost instant) responses and help over the last few days made 4 of our prospects (all from different companies) EXTREMELY happy in regards to getting into MnG's or getting theirs changed. So thank you both for the continued and tremendous work and urgency you put in to help not only us all internally, but our prospects too. Much appreciated!\n\n265#WorkHuman Content and Comms Command|Incredible job showcasing your amazing work for WorkHuman - and educating the entire company on its value.  WorkHuman is an enormous team effort for our entire content and communications strategy and execution.  From the start of planning last year until now, it's quite clear that not a single detail has been missed and we are maximizing each and every opportunity to leverage our relationships with speakers, prospects, partners, customers, and the Austin community.  So much of it is behind the scenes.  Thank you for all fantastic, thoughtful work - but even more importantly, thank you for your positivity, determination, and collaboration.  It's a key reason why 2018 will be another incredible event!\n\n266#Always Helping|Dan - Thank you for always being available at any time to help with content requests. There's been multiple projects lately that I've stopped you and asked if you could help weigh in on the content. You dropped what you were doing to immediately come help. Thanks for always being so supportive and working as a team on projects. It's nice to know that we have such a good resource and team player working with us!\n\n267#Appreciate all of your help!|This past week we decided to create some last minute social assets for Employee Appreciation Day. Even with your busy schedules you were both super quick to help in reviewing the copy so that we could get them posted on time. Thank you SO much, we truly appreciate you!!\n\n268#Meet & Greets|Dan, you've been a huge help in organizing meet & greets for WH18. You are full of insight and experience from managing it last year with Michelle Obama and additional keynotes. With nine high-level speakers this year there are many pieces to the meet & greet puzzle. Thank you for guiding me through the process this year.\n\n269#Process Followers!|Thank you for using Workfront to submit your recent request. Especially for not walking over and asking \"Do I really need to submit this through Workfront?\"   I appreciate you following the process, especially during WorkHuman Madness!\n\n270#Web Copy in a Jiffy|Thank you all for the speedy (1 day) turnaround on re-writing the content for our new core website pages.  Throughout this project, you have all been such amazing teammates and I could recognize you on an almost daily basis for your contributions.  This is a fast-moving project, but having the support of a great team makes it all achievable.\n\n271#Calming those first program jitters!|Thanks so much to an amazing content team for your support on my first demand campaign, focused around the SHRM report. You were all so helpful through your guidance around Workfront, approvals and brainstorming and refining the content pieces. I greatly appreciate the support and patience, you are all rockstars!!!\n\n272#\"Fate cannot harm me, I have dined today\"|Thank you all for making my first dine around experience such an awesome one!  You were all great dining companions - gracious, considerate, interesting, open and funny.  Kieran, your \"whale of a tale\" is a modern day Melville classic.  Todd, sorry to have missed out during your Carnival days, but I hope to hear you play piano sometime.  Melody, your martial arts skills sound impressive!  Derek, I had no idea I was dining in the presence of descended Irish gentry.  Julie, your kung fu skills made me feel safer that you were on the walk back to the hotel with all of us.  Dan, that Who concert sounds like a once in a lifetime experience!  Sophia, snowboarders rock!  Ken, your daughter will make the Navy proud someday.  Stacey, I really hope your kickboxing class comes to the Framingham office!  And yes, I'd take a great feeling over a great fact anytime, and the fact is you all gave me a great feeling that night.  Thank you!\n\n273#Support + wisdom + humility = a true leader|Dan, I‚Äôve only been at Globoforce little over two months and already I feel like this award is long overdue. Since my start date, I have felt nothing but support and guidance and kindness from you. In whatever task I‚Äôm given, you make sure to set me up for success. On top of this, you‚Äôre a person to emulate - your humility, your willingness to roll up your sleeves and help all who come to you, your commendable work ethic. I‚Äôve had many managers over the years - some excellent, others not so much - but I hadn‚Äôt been at work a full two weeks before I realized you‚Äôre in a different category. You‚Äôre the kind of person who is a mentor, and I‚Äôm truly grateful and excited to be part of your team. Thank you.\n\n274#The show must go on!|Team - Thank you all for keeping our campaigns on track this week, even while we were away at Ignite. With everyone busy and away from the office, and our laptops, you were determined to launch our SHRM Report and Top Reasons to attend WH campaigns. Thank you for going above and beyond during a very hectic few days!\n\n275#Working through Ignite|Thank you Dan for making time to help us when projects came through during Ignite. (And having no fear as I scouted you out in the hallway during breaks) You are so nice to work with and flexible as our schedules don‚Äôt always allow much time upfront for content. You are very well respected for all of the great work you do. Another congrats on your SLC Award as well. Much deserved! Thank you for all of your hard work and support.\n\n276#Fierce Timeframe|Angela said it best when she wrote \"team, we have a fierce timeframe project\" coming up. It was really important to pull together this Conversations webinar with so many moving parts. You each stepped up to the plate without any hesitation.  Dan, you had other critical projects last week and you always made this a priority even at the end of the day Friday.   Lauren, you handled all the complexity of the tone and messaging with expediency and high quality work. And making slight changes to everything during breaks at Ignite.  Angela, you didn't shy away from mobilizing the team for this project and staying on top of every aspect even here at Ignite. Thank you for everything you do!!!  Diane, you have an amazing work ethic. Your job is never easy and dealing with all the nuances with the lists, the landing page, the email invite changes, etc. for this project. You were on top of it every step along the way. You are always there to work through the differences in our customer marketing projects.   I can't thank you all enough and for working on this during breaks these last two days. With a deep appreciation and gratitude.\n\n277#Strength in numbers|It's all about teamwork. To quote Helen Keller, \"Alone we can do so little; together we can do so much.\" Eric Bauer and I would like to thank you for taking time last week to go through the new master sales deck we've been working on for the last couple of months. It was helpful to have fresh perspective and we appreciate all the suggestions you provided to tweak the language here and there, and adjust the cadence of the slides to keep the audience engaged. As we begin to share the deck with others, it continues to evolve AND become stronger. Your input is invaluable, and will help us achieve our goal of delivering the best sales pitch ever. Thanks again!\n\n278#Agility with a smile|I came in this morning with a series of content requests from our Web design agency -- items they needed to keep the website redesign project moving forward.  You both dropped everything else you were doing (and I know how busy you must be) to spend hours putting these materials together so that we could return them as quickly as possible.  I really appreciate this commitment to the website project, and your willingness to upend your day to keep us on the fast track.  Thank you boh.\n\n279#Breaking News!|Team - I loved the energy in the marketing area this morning ...it felt like a news room full of reporters covering a breaking story. You were all amazing, pulling together and getting the Ashley Judd announcement done and out the door in a matter of hours. It's exciting and fantastic to see what this team of determined, dedicated, creative experts can achieve together. You are the best team ever! Here's to reaching 1,000 by 12/31!\n\n280#Twists. Turns. Sprints. Moving Content Ahead.|Dan - The past few weeks have seen so many new projects, new concepts, and twists and turns to old projects - and everything in between. Quick pivots and new ideas are part of the Globoforce DNA and how and why we continue to innovate and lead. You are always quick to move, quick to help, and quick to produce high quality content and leadership for both Globoforce and WorkHuman marketing and sales.  Steady through it all. Thank you for always being such a great partner - someone who sees the big picture and the opportunity ahead. All of these projects and ideas culminate in new future wins and expansion in the industry for Globoforce!\n\n281#48 hours in Austin|Thank you all so much for a well planned, productive (and fun) site visit to Austin. The combination of all of your creative, logistics, content, and marketing expertise allowed us to quickly weigh the pros and cons of each venue, visualize the experience, and determine how and to who we'd message it. We have an amazing experience planned for the Executive Forum thanks to all of you!\n\n282#Focus on Executive Customers|Thanks so much for such an engaging ideation session with the SCD team last week!  So many great ideas for driving engagement at the most senior levels of our customers.  We are lucky to have such great partners in marketing who are thinking BIG about the kind of impact we can have on HR Leaders and the industry as a whole.  We are all super excited to get our 2018 customer marketing programs in motion.  Thanks for being such great partners!\n\n283#Who wouldn't want to come work with us!?|Thank you to this great team of people who wrote the copy, designed the ad, kept us on track, gave great feedback, incorporated that feedback, and to the subjects of our photo who so graciously and quickly agreed to be included, thank you! We often hear that sales is a team sport, and you know what else is? Recruitment advertising! Creating a great ad to draw people in when they're looking at The Boston Globe's Sunday Magazine on Nov 19 is no simple feat! Thanks to everyone involved for the role you played in getting this off to print and for helping raise awareness of Globoforce as a top place to work. Well done!\n\n284#Amazing team spirit|Dan, I am so struck by how often you go out of your way with an offer to help a team member with a project, often adding to your own considerable workload. I've come to you for input, as have other new folks in marketing, and you enthusiastically engage in the project at hand with not just great suggestions but hands-on help. Your instincts are to give real support to your team mate and improve the project for the good of the business. It is quite remarkable. I want to thank you and let you know you set a great example of teamwork every day.\n\n285#'It's all happening!'|Walking out of that fantastic presentation, all I could think of one of my favorite quotes from one of my favorite movies of all time, 'It's all happening!' - Almost Famous. You four put together GREAT out-of-the-box ideas that wowed Janet, Kevin and I. Ideas that we are