sh!\n\n289#ALL THE THINGS|I just love working with you. You come to every meeting pumped up and ready to give 110%. Your approach has been so collaborative, you've taken on more and more work from WorkHuman video outlines to the new Globoforce case study‚Äìrewritten a whole bunch of ads and other small things when I needed you to. I cannot thank you enough for all the work‚Äìbut more than that, it's the way you do it‚Äìalways forward and with a smile! Just thank you for being you.\n\n290#WorkHuman Roadshow|Rebecca, Alice, Dan and Jenn, Thank you for all the preparation for bringing and inspiring WorkHuman for the customer success team. Alice, you are such a \"champion\" for your team and together with Rebecca and the CSMs, you are strong advocates for our customers. Dan and Jenn, thank you again for another engaging presentation, putting together CS specific content, supporting me in my first presentation and igniting the kick-off's. Here's to the next roadshow!\n\n291#amazing video for Accenture RFI|Jess and Matt - thank you so much for taking my vision for the Executive Summary and making it into a phenomenal visual experience for our prospect!  From the quality of the video to the heartfelt message you all used your expertise to show how and why Globoforce is the right partner for Accenture.  Our company has worked this account for 5 years and we know so much about them and all of that came across in this video.  What a great way to differentiate Globoforce right from the start.  Our team will continue to run with it and make all of our hard work worth it!\n\n292#Content team to the rescue!|Thank you for your willingness to help carry all of the printed pieces in your suitcases for HR Tech! In doing this, you allowed us time to get them printed at a much better quality and saved the company what could have been thousands of dollars. I appreciate you working together to split the bundles to help save each other on extra weight! True team effort!\n\n293#Fresh and so clean clean|Team- From the very beginning everyone was a bit skeptical about refreshing our fabulous Hello-box, however the new design is so fresh and so clean! The work that went into this from the design, vendor updates, spec and pricing, meetings and reviews was endless. Every time we thought we had covered everything something else was thought of...a sign of true collaboration! So incredibly excited about all the new design and the additional offerings available to our stakeholders!!\n\n294#OOO Calendar|Thank you for using the OOO calendar so Angela and I are equipped to schedule meetings and deadlines. It is a small task that makes a big difference in managing your projects; we appreciate it!\n\n295#Meeting Coverage|Dan - Thank you for offering to cover for me today at a meeting where I was scheduled to present. I was not feeling well and you quickly offered to stand in for me so I could go home and rest. It was a very busy Monday for all of us, and I appreciate you taking this on today. You're a great teammate!\n\n296#Wile E. Coyote Cannot Catch You|Angela and Dan, thank you very much for your quick response to my request for content for the Accenture Premium Awards presentation.  You each managed you aspect of this project with the highest level of urgency given our short turn-around time and importance of this deal.  I am alway impressed by your professionalism.  Now, you've blown me away with your speed to complete the work.  Great job.\n\n297#Speedy reviews, day or night|Dan, I really appreciate your feedback on the blogs, and often on a very tight turnaround - sometimes involving nights and weekends or even just a couple of hours!  You are always there with a speedy response and thoughtful comments to improve the text. I'm always looking to be a better writer and you definitely help me to do that. Thanks!\n\n298#Holiday weekend urgent request|Eric/Dan- Thank you so much for your quick turnaround on the differentiator slide for the Frontier Communications presentation. It was an urgent request and a holiday weekend. I appreciate your dedication!\n\n299#Dedicated Detective at SHRM|Dan - Excellent work at SHRM last week playing the role of our recognition detective!  Staying ahead also means looking behind sometimes. You were able to glean some fantastic insights and competitive learnings from your work on the floor - asking the right questions in a very detailed way. These types of competitive insights are invaluable as we continue to fight the good fight to win in 2017 and beyond.\n\n300#Healthcare Content|Aaron and Dan,  Thank you for all of your help on the content for the healthcare campaign. We are ready to launch this campaign and couldn't have done it without your help. There were several different email versions that needed to be created and you made sure it was all completed and ready to go ahead of schedule. It is extremely valuable that we are able to make this campaign so targeted by focusing the messaging on individual job functions. Thank you for your expertise and attention to detail. Looking forward to working together on many more projects!\n\n301#Anything Goes|Thank you so much for all of your help with arranging meet and greets at Work Human. I came to you with some last minute changes which you were happy to help with.  THEN, I came to you with a request to add one of my clients to meet Adam Grant.  The client was already scheduled for another session but REALLY wanted to meet him.  You didn't hesitate and made it happen.  Not only did she get to meet Adam Grant, she also got to attend her original meet and greet session.  I really appreciate all you did to make this client happy.  You didn't know it at the time, but her company is a top 10 Great Places to Work winner for their industry.  You helped her see just how great Globoforce is and how we made it on to the list as well!\n\n302#The Action Behind the Action Plan|Team - Amazing teamwork on the WorkHuman action plan campaign!!! And yes, it de