rk.  Every single time I asked you to provide something, you did it quickly, efficiently and perfectly,  Your understanding of our audience base and their overall experience was spot-on.  And I know I learned a great deal from you over the past 5 months.  I also appreciate your grounded perspective and positive mindset.  In a crazy environment that is so important and I know your mindset helped me many times!  A tremendous thank you and I look forward to WH18!\n\n"
"306#The WorkHuman Roller Coaster|Dan - Thank you for all of your fantastic work both directing and contributing to the excellent new content published during the conference. The newsroom was certainly cranking out the highlights at lightning speed.  In addition to this, we had a potentially challenging situation come up that requirement immediate action - you jumped on this and made things happen.  During the course of conference, many different things arise but I'm thankful to have your steady leadership at every step.\n\n307#Content is King|I just wanted to take a moment after all these months of insanity to thank you for all the thoughtful, focused, collaborative moments that it has taken to promote, build and evolve everything that is WorkHuman. From every blog post, press release, social post, ad headline, and email down to the tiniest of blurbs on every piece of signage you have helped shape our voice and created a meaningful experience for everyone who interacts with us. It has been amazing to work with you all or just see the work fly by ‚Äì without your fabulous words and message our team is just pushing pixels! Thank you so much for all that you do!\n\n308#Let's have a conversation|I wanted to take a minute to thank this incredible team for rallying around the new conversations landing page. We needed a quick asset to release at workhuman, and all of you jumped on it, despite full schedules and a tight timeline. I think the finished project will be perfect for what we are trying to accomplish, and we never could have done it without all of you. Thank you!\n\n309#Master of the Meet and Greets|Dan - thank you for doing such a masterful job managing the Meet and Greets for WorkHuman.  This is not an easy project.  It's a constant juggle that involves many people - to ensure we are fully leveraging these opportunities to enhance our relationships with both customers and prospects.  This experience is an important part of WorkHuman for many of these attendees.  Thank for all of your efforts and for continuing to maintain your positivity throughout.  Kevin\n\n310#WorkHuman Content Overload|Thank you for all of your hard work managing multiple pieces of content for WorkHuman and especially with the interviews for WorkHuman Radio. You are working on so many aspects of the conference, I'm amazed you are able to keep all the different balls in the air. Thank you!\n\n311#Regional Respect|hey Dan, thanks for going outside of your role and helping with greeting of customers and prospects at Workhuman London. I found it a unique experience to do this at such a great venue with you. Your natural charm was really welcoming at 9 a.m on a cold London morning. The content for the event was superb and has really helped with the follow up. Thanks and great to meet and spend some time with you!\n\n312#Know I know, and knowing is half the battle|Pam, Dan, & Holly -- What a great presentation you put together to get the whole marketing team informed on your post-WorkHuman ABM/Content Strategy.  You really hit the right notes giving context and background to each element of your plan, and just the right information so we all know what's in store but weren't bogged down in details. I came away feeling smarter about our strategy and more connected to your part of our team -- thanks!\n\n313#Dan the Man!|Dan - partnering with you on numerous WorkHuman projects over the last few weeks has been such a pleasure! You are focused, calm, and determined, all great qualities when it's crunch time! I can't wait to see meet and greets, round tables, and WH follow-up plans come to life!\n\n314#Your Time & Expertise|Dan,   Thank you so much for lending a hand to my rough draft following up my discussion with the EVP of People & Comms at American Airlines. I knew the topics I wanted to cover in my follow up but for the life of me couldn't encapsulate all of that into a reasonable sized email. It was Friday afternoon when we connected about this and you could've said no that you didn't have the time, but you said yes even though you truly didn't have the time. You had your daughter's dance competition all weekend but still found the time to get me a revised email at 2 pm on Saturday. Your work ethic, professionalism and sense of urgency is very much appreciated and I can't thank you enough!\n\n315#Thank you for your brain power!|Thank you for participating in the brainstorm to help us develop answers on behalf of the company for the Great Place to Work survey. The employee portion is now complete, and now we're tasked with writing about what it's like to work here and the programs and perks we offer. Thank you for talking through what you think makes Globoforce great, and for helping us think about the stories we have to tell and the photos we can share to bring our story to life. \"Teamwork makes the dream work.\" Thank you, for being part of this team!\n\n316#Dan-tastic!|Dan, thanks so much for re-arranging your work yesterday to fit in my small emergencies. There was a few fires needing attention you you graciously offered to stop and work on the job at hand. I appreciate your super attitude and fast proofing/writing. Thanks for all you do to make GF sound great!\n\n317#So many eyes|Over the past week you've been buried in proofs for notebooks and signs and more. So. Many. Proofs. We're not quite done yet, but 'almost there' feels like the time to share my appreciation for all your time, patience, not running away when you see me chasing you down.... Thank you for using the tool, adapting to it, learning on the fly. I can't wait to see everything printed and enjoyed by all attendees, and to share the group exhale with you! Thank you, teammates.\n\n318#The content master!|Dan, thank you so much for joining the west coast team call on Monday to review our content requirements and provide contextual input. During the past several months you've made a tremendous impact to the sales team, to help us locate the exact piece of collateral we need to address client pain points, awareness and customer enablement. We really appreciate your can-do attitude and support. Many thanks again Dan!!\n\n319#RFP Product Messaging Review|Dan,  I just finished making your updates and added in new messaging for the RFP DB. Thank you for working so diligently to get this content reviewed, updated and back to me. This new messaging that revolves around our thought leadership, IBM Index, WorkHuman, Innovation, etc. is what will set us apart with both our prospects and existing customers. I know reviewing all of this content can be a herculean effort, and my team appreciates you stepping up to make us better. Your work will help us get to the next level of the sales evaluation.  Thank you,  Michael\n\n320#Leading our Content to New Heights|Dan - It's unbelievable to think you've only been at Globoforce for 6.5 months. During that time, you've made a remarkable impact in bringing our content marketing to a whole new level. Since you started, you immediately jumped in and filled our content gaps - and in the process became a trusted leader and partner to both sales and marketing.  You display a level of determination and steadiness, alongside great enthusiasm and positivity, in producing a continuous feed of stellar work (from WorkHuman to sales to collateral to the web to much more!). No matter the project, you are always willing to jump in and help.  Thank you for all of your efforts.  The future is so bright for our content.  Thank you!\n\n321#Bridging the Gap|Thank you so much for putting together such a detailed brief for our new \"bridge the gap\" campaign.\n\n322#Flash Miller|Dan,  I can't thank you enough. Once we got word that First Lady Michelle Obama was speaking at WorkHuman, I had an idea to reach out to all Chief Diversity Officers in my territory. I came to you for help in creating an email that would catch their attention. You had 2 emails for me the next morning. Last night I used them and within 30 minutes of sending the email, responses started to come in. You are now my go to guy for creating attention grabbing emails.   Miguel\n\n323#WorkHuman Announcement Engine|The journey to publicly announce WorkHuman keynotes is a winding road of twists and turns. Stops and starts. Hidden cliffs and long straight drives to the end.  There are so many parts that play into a successful launch - and making everything look and sound great internally and externally and getting the wide world ready to embrace the share news, updates, and more.  Thank you to all of you of your continued fantastic work, patience, attitude, and diligence in making this year's WorkHuman line-up a sure-fire promo hit!\n\n324#Hmmm..how about....can we....|Dan, we have been going a million miles an hour the last two weeks for project MO and you have been a pleasure to work with. No matter what sales asked for from you, you put something fantastic together. Even as people changed their minds, asked for new things, or gave their opinions and edits, you did it with a phenomenal attitude and acted as a true partner. I cant thank you enough, you are a big part of everything we do!\n\n325#Tremendous Team Effort|Thank you all for your contribution to open up a new innovative opportunity for us to connect to customers focused on Diversity and Inclusion by illustrating to them how recognition is tightly connected to their D&I goals. Each of you collaborated and contributed to the Sales collateral that is field ready thanks to your imagination and determination. Lynette and Greg, I can't thank you enough for making the connection between the Belonging data from the GF/IBM EE Experience survey and inclusion. That data unlocked our ability to ask \"How are you measuring inclusion?\" to a whole new crop of prospects who I'd bet are challenged to measure it as easily as they can with strategic and social recognition. Dan and Amanda, thank you for listening to our innovative ideas and pulling the story together with compelling images and speaking notes. Even through the Saturday before I was presenting our ideas, you were both actively engaged and determined to put our best foot forward with external ready materials. Kevin, I could not have had such a complete set of materials without having your commitment, engagement and support of your team, not to mention your involvement over the weekend and morning of the presentation with up to the minute communication of D&I champions committed to WorkHuman. I sense another movement happening and I'm proud to work with each and every one of you - thank you for seeing and being committed to the vision.\n\n326#Volumes of stuff!|Dan - the amount of high quality content that you churn out is quite amazing.  I don't know how you do it, but you deliver, and deliver, and you keep delivering.  There is so much going on at GF these days, and so many roads lead back to content - and you are right there with thoughtful, strategic, high-quality, relevant stuff - all the time.  I'm sure you are looking to come up for air - but in the meantime I just wanted to let you know how valued you are.  Thanks for your on going contributions.\n\n327#Keeping Content Current|Thank you, Dan, for reviewing and rewriting large sections of globoforce.com to ensure that our messaging is current and accurate.  This was a project that was sorely needed and a gap in our messaging that I am very happy to have closed.  Great work!\n\n328#Crossing the i's and dotting the t's with a smile|Your eye for detail is impeccable! Your commitment to deliver quality content is remarkable! Your willingness to help is commendable! I can't thank you enough for always making yourself available to proof my copy. No matter how busy you are, you make it a priority to proof any content I send your way. And, you always catch stuff not visible to the naked eye:) It's so great to have you as the final line of defense!\n\n329#Crowdsourcing Award Names!|Dan - thank for your great name for one of our customer awards at WorkHuman. It was the perfect way to describe the award and I know the winners will be thrilled to win it at WorkHuman. Thanks so much for your teamwork and helping us \" crowdsource\" ideas.\n\n330#WorkHuman CHRO Outreach Campaign|Team - THANK YOU all so very much for your fabulous work on the WorkHuman CHRO outreach campaign. AMC and Anthony - amazing support creating 9 lists, Jen and Kelli - impactful designs for online and offline assets, Matt and Brian - quick turnaround on a new site and lots of requested changes, Aaron and Dan - fresh, compelling messages for this executive audience, Jill - setting up a custom CHRO registration experience, Stacey - getting the video of Eric done (and then redone), and of course Dianne for keeping us on track and on task! Great teamwork everyone!\n\n331#Mindful Meetings - Doing it Right!|I wanted to call out your participation in a wider team meeting we had yesterday.  It was such a great example of doing a meeting right here at Globoforce.  It was collaborative.  It was engaging.  It was open.  You all shared ideas - but also shared concerns about ways we could approach different opportunities - things that could make us more productive.  Questions were asked.  Solutions were brought to the table - with people building ideas off each other.  And it was also fun!  It should be the model for all the meetings we have here.  Great job!\n\n332#Hitting the Heart of the Message and Opportunity!|Dan - Awesome work in translating our new WorkHuman messaging approach into the CHRO collateral piece (and other associated communications).  You took our new opportunity to heart and the messaging came across really well.  This is going to be instrumental in the recruitment efforts - and getting HR leaders to see and know that WorkHuman is the place for senior leaders to go if they want to bring out the best in their people, their culture, and their business!  Kevin\n\n333#meeting madness|I just wanted to give you a shout out for the many meetings we've had this week-you've been my super partner. Thank you for always advocating for better process and understanding so we can really get the best out of the projects that are in place. You've been a calm and determined voice and you remind me that we're going to get there!\n\n334#Kicking off a revolution|When we needed to brainstorm some new campaign concepts for WorkHuman this week, you all jumped on board, immediately throwing out creative and fresh ideas. The resulting campaign concepts are original, timely, and impactful and I can't wait to see how they perform in market.\n\n335#Why? Why? Why?|Dan - thank you for jumping in and delivering updated web copy for the WorkHuman 2017 web site.  We needed compelling content around WHY clients and prospects should attend the event and you provided hard hitting, valuable copy that we will be able to use in many of our assets and tactics going forward. I look forward to seeing it help in our drive-to activities.  Sharing the why really completes the whole story for us!  Thank you!\n\n336#ABM at Ignite (X4)|Pam and Dan -  A huge shout out to both of you for a fantastic job with your ABM/Content presentation at Ignite.  For starters, Pam did an outstanding job giving ABM the definition and the context that was needed for everyone to understand how this new strategy will help drive conversion and impact the business.  Dan connected the dots to the content that is so critical to support this strategy.  You both demonstrated an understanding of the business, and the needs of the sales organization.  There was applause (i.e for the new Eaton case study); comments (i.e. \"I now understand what Marketing does\"); and a ton of positive feedback.  Your presentation was engaging as it delivered new ideas, new content and a new structure that is needed to hit the ground running in 2017.  I know how difficult it can be to deliver the presentation 4 times in a row, and you guys were fantastic.  Congrats on a job well done.\n\n337#Steering the Content Ship in 2017|Dan - I wanted to take a moment to thank you for all of your remarkable efforts in the past few weeks.  There has been a great deal of new content ready for sales use (and much on the way).  You've also created a strong content calendar for 2017 - which will help many collective teams plan and prepare for the year ahead.  Finally, you stepped up and helped delivered a great breakout session at Ignite - to show the organization where content is heading in the months ahead.  Thank you for your continued enthusiasm, expert guidance, and leadership.  So much goodness ahead.  Kevin\n\n338#Pivotal Peeps|Just wanted to give a shout out for some awesome go-to attitudes! It's hard to turn on a dime and with the WH.com efforts that have been in process suddenly needing to take a new direction, you all came with your \"yes and\" on and solutions at the ready. I love working with this team because everyone is so willing to do whatever is necessary to succeed‚Äìno egos and no naysayers. I know that we're putting the right people on this project and the end result is going to be amazing! THANK YOU!\n\n339#Marketing Hackathon Success|Thank you for making the first-ever Marketing Hackathon such a success! You embodied all our core values and the results were fantastic. The two-week Marketing sprint made us more agile as a team, brought out new ideas empowering every member of the team, and we found new approaches to market ‚Äì ideas that could impact both our marketing approach and our go-to market for opportunities ahead. There was a buzz and vibe around the office that was felt by all your enthusiasm and accomplishment - all the way up the executive chain. Simply put, YOU ROCKED IT! Jess, Jill, and Kevin\n\n340#Stepping Up for WorkHuman!!|Dan and Aaron, Thank you both so much for putting together the Sell Sheet for WorkHuman.  This is a great tool to consolidate all the different messaging, events, updates and all the goings on of WorkHuman.  As we add things to use to drive attendance, you came to me and asked what we could use to better keep track of everything to make sure we had easy access to everything we have.  Thank you for producing this and getting to the team.  Its going to help us drive great attendance to a great event.  Thanks!\n\n341#WorkFront Pro in the making|Dan, you have only been here a short amount of time, and as I am starting to collaborate with you on more and more projects, I am noticing how efficient and timely you are when it comes to working in WorkFront. Your response time is within the hour and you always make sure to tag the correct people on the project. This is incredibly helpful to me when working on a campaign and juggling creative reviews. You are already using the proofing tool and markups correctly and this just goes to show how quickly you are adapting to working in WorkFront! Thank you so much for sticking to the tool!\n\n342#So Much Content, So Little Time|Dan, Just want to send a quick note to express my gratitude for your teamwork since coming on board not even two months ago. In particular, you've jumped right in to thoughtfully review and proofread blogs, eBooks, research reports, emails - the list goes on! You're also super responsive, often sending back reviewed content the same day I send it to you. You've quickly become an integral part of the content machine and I'm so happy you are here! Thank you!\n\n343#Product and Content Marketing for the Win|Dan, thank you for your support, input, and drive to create the internal product and content marketing survey.  I appreciate the time that you dedicated to this project and am excited about the feedback we'll get from our sales team.  Your calm demeanor and extensive knowledge made teaming with you on this project a absolute pleasure.  I look forward to collaborating with you on future marketing projects, deciphering the data from this survey, and making an action plan based on the survey results.  Thank you and great job.\n\n344#The Brady Bunch|Kelli, Lisa, Dianne, Aaron and Dan- First of all, wow not even sure where to begin! Kelli/Lisa-  From the beginning you both really took this and ran with it!  It was a calendar coaster, then a calendar, and now a beautifully designed coaster that everyone just has to have! Dianne- Managing these changes was no small feat! You did it with such ease and kept us all organized. Aaron/Dan- The strong message and brand awareness brought into this really unique concept, was quite a challenge. Thank you so much for your dedication to perfecting and getting the final copy JUST right! I am so overwhelmed by the dedication from all of you and cannot wait to see results!!\n\n345#Making Holidays Happy!|Dan -  Thank you so much for all of your help in writing the copy for the holiday cards for 2016.  The beautiful sentiments you captured for our contacts in both the US and Europe will surely bring cheer to our customers and prospects when they receive their cards. Thank you for your help!\n\n346#Big Efforts Right Out of the Gates!|Dan - I've been greatly impressed by your efforts here at Globoforce - in a very short amount of time.  You've jumped right in with great ideas, sound strategic thinking, and a willingness to help in many areas (including gaps you saw).  To date, you've built a new messaging hierarchy for WorkHuman, started the 2017 content calendar, and so much more!  Thank you for your great enthusiasm and I look forward to the many great things to come out of content in 2017 and beyond!   Kevin\n\n347#Team spirit|Dan and Amanda,  Thank you for all your help with the CR Forum slide deck.  Amanda, you jumped on the edits right away and pulled the deck together! You have a great eye and excellent suggestions on how to make the content stand out! I really appreciate it.  Dan, thank you for your work on the title! You are always willing to lend a hand to take the content a notch higher and ensure quality control.  Lucky to have team mates like you!\n\n348#Catalyst Awards Ad|Creating an inspiring ad for Globoforce, tied to Boston's Science Club for Girls, for their Catalyst Awards program guide was a challenge you accepted! The timeline was tight, the space to fill was small, and after a couple of iterations we had the text, nailed the design and finished prior to the publication deadline. Amazing teamwork, project management and creativity on all fronts. Thank you for your help creating this ad, to which my contact said \"I LOVE this ad!\"\n\n349#Writing The Next Great Content Chapter|Dan - welcome to Globoforce!  You're a most welcome addition to the team.  You've only been here a week - but you're already making an impact, jumping in with great enthusiasm to projects.  In fact, you already contributed with great copy for an ad just a few days after you started.  Thank you for the energy and passion you've brought with you - an eagerness to learn our business, get to know your colleagues, and starting to build out the content vision.  I look forward to the months and years ahead!   Kevin\n\n"
